1
00:01:16,618 --> 00:01:19,121 
I believe in America.

2
00:01:19,496 --> 00:01:21,999 
America has made my fortune

3
00:01:22,583 --> 00:01:25,085 
and I raised my daughter
in the American fashion.

4
00:01:26,753 --> 00:01:29,548 
I gave her freedom,
but I taught her

5
00:01:29,631 --> 00:01:32,134 
never to dishonor her family.

6
00:01:33,010 --> 00:01:36,221 
She found a boyfriend.
Not an Italian.

7
00:01:36,346 --> 00:01:38,682 
She went to the movies with him.

8
00:01:38,682 --> 00:01:41,768 
She stayed out late.
I didn't protest.

9
00:01:43,562 --> 00:01:46,398 
Two months ago,
he took her for a drive

10
00:01:46,481 --> 00:01:48,984 
with another boyfriend.

11
00:01:49,318 --> 00:01:51,945 
They made her drink whiskey,

12
00:01:52,070 --> 00:01:55,240 
and then they tried
to take advantage of her.

13
00:01:56,491 --> 00:01:58,660 
She resisted.

14
00:01:58,660 --> 00:02:01,163 
She kept her honor.

15
00:02:01,914 --> 00:02:04,917 
So they beat her like an animal.

16
00:02:06,877 --> 00:02:10,547 
When I went to the hospital,
her nose was broken...

17
00:02:11,882 --> 00:02:14,009 
her jaw was shattered...

18
00:02:14,009 --> 00:02:16,512 
held together by wire.

19
00:02:18,555 --> 00:02:21,099 
She couldn't even weep
because of the pain.

20
00:02:23,936 --> 00:02:27,439 
But I wept.
Why did I weep?

21
00:02:30,108 --> 00:02:32,611 
She was the light of my life.

22
00:02:34,488 --> 00:02:36,990 
Beautiful girl.

23
00:02:39,952 --> 00:02:42,454 
Now she will never
be beautiful again.

24
00:02:49,628 --> 00:02:52,130 
Sorry.

25
00:03:00,264 --> 00:03:02,766 
I, I went to the police,
like a good American.

26
00:03:03,809 --> 00:03:06,311 
These two boys
were brought to trial.

27
00:03:07,646 --> 00:03:10,399 
A judge sentence them
to three years in prison...

28
00:03:10,482 --> 00:03:12,985 
and suspend their sentence.

29
00:03:13,819 --> 00:03:16,321 
Suspended the sentence.

30
00:03:16,363 --> 00:03:18,866 
They went free that very day.

31
00:03:21,034 --> 00:03:23,537 
I stood in the courtroom
like a fool.

32
00:03:24,413 --> 00:03:27,666 
And those two bastard,
they smiled at me.

33
00:03:29,251 --> 00:03:32,671 
Then I said to my wife,
"For justice...

34
00:03:32,796 --> 00:03:35,299 
we must go to Don Corleone."

35
00:03:40,179 --> 00:03:43,515 
Why did you go to the police?
Why didn't you come to me first?

36
00:03:44,683 --> 00:03:46,518 
What do you want of me?

37
00:03:46,518 --> 00:03:49,605 
Tell me anything,
but do what I beg you to do.

38
00:03:50,814 --> 00:03:53,317 
What is that?

39
00:04:17,216 --> 00:04:19,718 
That I cannot do.

40
00:04:20,219 --> 00:04:22,721 
I'll give you anything you ask.

41
00:04:25,098 --> 00:04:27,893 
We've known each other many years,
but this is the first time...

42
00:04:27,976 --> 00:04:31,313 
you ever came to me
for counsel or for help.

43
00:04:31,396 --> 00:04:34,358 
I can't remember the last time
that you invited me...

44
00:04:34,441 --> 00:04:36,944 
to your house
for a cup of coffee...

45
00:04:38,028 --> 00:04:41,698 
even though my wife
is godmother to your only child.

46
00:04:41,782 --> 00:04:44,076 
But let's be frank.

47
00:04:44,076 --> 00:04:46,578 
You never wanted my friendship...

48
00:04:47,079 --> 00:04:50,707 
and you were afraid
to be in my debt.

49
00:04:50,791 --> 00:04:53,293 
I didn't want
to get into trouble.

50
00:04:54,419 --> 00:04:56,922 
I understand.

51
00:04:57,297 --> 00:04:59,800 
You found paradise in America.

52
00:05:02,594 --> 00:05:04,596 
You had a good trade,
you made a good living.

53
00:05:04,596 --> 00:05:07,307 
Police protected you,
and there were courts of law.

54
00:05:07,432 --> 00:05:09,935 
So you didn't need
a friend like me.

55
00:05:11,770 --> 00:05:15,315 
But, now you come to me
and you say,

56
00:05:15,440 --> 00:05:17,943 
"Don Corleone, give me justice."

57
00:05:19,653 --> 00:05:22,531 
But you don't ask with respect.

58
00:05:22,614 --> 00:05:25,200 
You don't offer friendship.

59
00:05:25,284 --> 00:05:27,786 
You don't even think
to call me 'Godfather.'

60
00:05:28,954 --> 00:05:30,747 
Instead, you come into my house

61
00:05:30,747 --> 00:05:32,749 
on the day my daughter
is to be married

62
00:05:32,749 --> 00:05:35,252 
and you ask me to do murder
for money.

63
00:05:36,086 --> 00:05:38,630 
I ask you for justice.

64
00:05:38,755 --> 00:05:41,466 
That is not justice.
Your daughter is still alive.

65
00:05:42,801 --> 00:05:46,138 
They must suffer then
as she suffers.

66
00:05:48,223 --> 00:05:50,726 
How much shall I pay you?

67
00:06:05,282 --> 00:06:07,784 
Bonasera. Bonasera.

68
00:06:09,328 --> 00:06:12,664 
What have I ever done to make you
treat me so disrespectfully?

69
00:06:14,500 --> 00:06:17,044 
If you'd come to me
in friendship,

70
00:06:17,169 --> 00:06:19,171 
then the scum
that ruined your daughter

71
00:06:19,171 --> 00:06:21,673 
would be suffering
this very day.

72
00:06:22,633 --> 00:06:23,884 
And if, by chance,

73
00:06:23,884 --> 00:06:25,969 
an honest man like yourself
should make enemies,

74
00:06:25,969 --> 00:06:28,472 
then they would become
my enemies.

75
00:06:30,557 --> 00:06:33,060 
And then they would fear you.

76
00:06:37,147 --> 00:06:39,650 
Be my friend?

77
00:06:43,070 --> 00:06:45,572 
Godfather.

78
00:06:49,159 --> 00:06:51,662 
Good.

79
00:06:52,329 --> 00:06:54,706 
Someday, and that day
may never come...

80
00:06:54,706 --> 00:06:57,209 
I'll call upon you
to do a service for me.

81
00:06:59,002 --> 00:07:01,505 
But until that day...

82
00:07:02,756 --> 00:07:05,759 
accept this justice as a gift
on my daughter's wedding day.

83
00:07:07,219 --> 00:07:09,721 
<i>- Grazie, Godfather.</i>
- Prego

84
00:07:16,770 --> 00:07:19,273 
Give this to Clemenza.

85
00:07:21,775 --> 00:07:23,235 
I want reliable people,

86
00:07:23,235 --> 00:07:25,404 
people that aren't
going to be carried away.

87
00:07:25,404 --> 00:07:26,947 
I mean, we're not murderers,

88
00:07:26,947 --> 00:07:29,533 
in spite of what
this undertaker says.

89
00:07:54,850 --> 00:07:56,518 
- Where's Michael?
- What? Don't worry.

90
00:07:56,518 --> 00:07:58,270 
It's early. He'll be here.

91
00:07:58,270 --> 00:07:59,521 
We're not taking it.

92
00:07:59,521 --> 00:08:02,024 
We're not taking the picture
without Michael.

93
00:08:02,524 --> 00:08:04,526 
<i>No picture now.</i>

94
00:08:08,405 --> 00:08:10,908 
- What's the matter, Sonny?
- It's Michael.

95
00:09:00,916 --> 00:09:03,418 
Don Barzini.

96
00:09:05,921 --> 00:09:07,923 
<i>Welcome to our house.</i>

97
00:09:19,142 --> 00:09:22,271 
Hey, Paulie!
Let me have some wine.

98
00:09:22,354 --> 00:09:24,940 
Paulie! More wine.

99
00:09:25,023 --> 00:09:26,316 
<i>Scusi, please.</i>

100
00:09:26,316 --> 00:09:28,151 
You look terrif on the floor.

101
00:09:28,151 --> 00:09:30,654 
What are you,
a dance judge or something?

102
00:09:31,655 --> 00:09:34,157 
Go take a walk around
the neighborhood. Do your job.

103
00:09:41,707 --> 00:09:43,709 
Hey, Sandra, come on. Do me a favor.
Watch the kids.

104
00:09:43,709 --> 00:09:46,670 
- Don't let 'em run wild, all right?
- Well, you watch yourself, all right?

105
00:10:08,817 --> 00:10:11,111 
Twenty or thirty grand.

106
00:10:11,111 --> 00:10:13,614 
In small bills, cash.

107
00:10:13,947 --> 00:10:16,450 
In that little silk purse.

108
00:10:16,909 --> 00:10:19,411 
Maron, if this was someone else's wedding, sweet
tonato!

109
00:10:20,078 --> 00:10:22,873 
<i>Hey, Paulie!</i>
I got two gobbagool...

110
00:10:22,956 --> 00:10:24,833 
<i>gabagol and a prosciutto.</i>

111
00:10:24,833 --> 00:10:27,336 
Stupid jerk!

112
00:10:35,552 --> 00:10:38,055 
Hey, what's the matter?

113
00:10:49,608 --> 00:10:52,027 
- I have to go back to work.
- Oh, Tom.

114
00:10:52,027 --> 00:10:53,362 
It's part of the wedding.

115
00:10:53,362 --> 00:10:56,281 
No Sicilian can refuse any request
on his daughter's wedding day.

116
00:11:02,287 --> 00:11:04,623 
Don Corleone,
I am honored and grateful...

117
00:11:04,623 --> 00:11:07,125 
that you have invited me
to your home...

118
00:11:11,797 --> 00:11:13,006 
Get outta here.

119
00:11:13,006 --> 00:11:15,509 
This is a private party.
Go on.

120
00:11:16,468 --> 00:11:18,971 
What is it?
Hey, my sister's wedding.

121
00:11:26,019 --> 00:11:28,522 
Goddamn FBI
don't respect nothin'.

122
00:11:31,191 --> 00:11:34,486 
Hey, come here, come here.
Come here!

123
00:11:35,863 --> 00:11:38,365 
There.

124
00:11:49,293 --> 00:11:51,378 
But towards the end
he was paroled...

125
00:11:51,378 --> 00:11:54,006 
to help with
the American war effort.

126
00:11:54,131 --> 00:11:56,633 
For the last six months, he's been
working at my pastry shop.

127
00:11:57,217 --> 00:11:59,386 
Nazorine, my friend,
what can I do for you?

128
00:11:59,386 --> 00:12:01,889 
Now that the war is over...

129
00:12:01,972 --> 00:12:05,017 
this boy, Enzo, they want
to repatriate him back to Italy.

130
00:12:06,143 --> 00:12:08,687 
Godfather, I have a daughter.

131
00:12:08,812 --> 00:12:11,315 
See, she and Enzo...

132
00:12:12,232 --> 00:12:14,318 
You want Enzo to stay
in this country...

133
00:12:14,318 --> 00:12:16,820 
and you want your daughter
to be married.

134
00:12:17,863 --> 00:12:20,365 
You understand everything.

135
00:12:21,074 --> 00:12:23,577 
Mr. Hagen. Thank you.

136
00:12:26,163 --> 00:12:28,165 
And wait till you see
the beautiful wedding cake...

137
00:12:28,165 --> 00:12:29,583 
I made for your daughter.

138
00:12:29,583 --> 00:12:32,169 
Like this, with the bride
and the groom and...

139
00:12:38,425 --> 00:12:41,512 
- Who should I give this job to?
- Not to our paisan.

140
00:12:43,222 --> 00:12:45,807 
Give it to a Jew congressman
in another district.

141
00:12:46,934 --> 00:12:49,436 
Who else is on the list?

142
00:12:55,567 --> 00:12:57,778 
Hey, Michael.
How are you?

143
00:12:57,778 --> 00:13:00,280 
Hello.

144
00:13:16,964 --> 00:13:19,716 
He's not on the list,
but Luca Brasi wants to see you.

145
00:13:26,139 --> 00:13:28,475 
Is this... Is this necessary?

146
00:13:28,475 --> 00:13:30,435 
He didn't expect to be invited
to the wedding...

147
00:13:30,435 --> 00:13:32,479 
so he wanted to thank you.

148
00:13:32,479 --> 00:13:34,189 
All right.

149
00:13:34,189 --> 00:13:37,401 
Don Corleone,
I am honored and grateful...

150
00:13:37,526 --> 00:13:40,028 
that you have invited me
to your home...

151
00:13:40,112 --> 00:13:42,614 
on the wedding day
of your daughter.

152
00:13:43,031 --> 00:13:45,534 
And may their first child
be a masculine child.

153
00:13:45,617 --> 00:13:48,162 
- Don...
- Michael?

154
00:13:48,287 --> 00:13:49,830 
Don Corleone...

155
00:13:49,830 --> 00:13:52,332 
That man over there
is talking to himself.

156
00:13:53,250 --> 00:13:55,752 
See that scary guy over there?

157
00:13:56,295 --> 00:13:57,588 
He's a very scary guy.

158
00:13:57,588 --> 00:13:59,923 
Who is he?
What's his name?

159
00:13:59,923 --> 00:14:02,509 
His name is Luca Brasi...

160
00:14:02,634 --> 00:14:05,137 
and he helps my father out
sometimes.

161
00:14:05,721 --> 00:14:08,432 
Oh, Michael, wait a minute.
He's coming over here.

162
00:14:08,432 --> 00:14:09,433 
Mike!

163
00:14:09,433 --> 00:14:10,934 
Ho! Tom.

164
00:14:10,934 --> 00:14:12,436 
Heyyy!

165
00:14:13,604 --> 00:14:15,480 
You look terrific!

166
00:14:15,480 --> 00:14:17,691 
My brother Tom Hagen.
This is Kay Adams.

167
00:14:17,691 --> 00:14:20,235 
- How do you do?
- Nice to meet you.

168
00:14:20,319 --> 00:14:22,696 
Your father's
been asking for you.

169
00:14:22,696 --> 00:14:24,448 
- Very nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

170
00:14:24,448 --> 00:14:26,950 
I'll be there.

171
00:14:27,326 --> 00:14:29,995 
If he's your brother,
why does he have a different name?

172
00:14:31,121 --> 00:14:33,123 
Oh, uh, when my brother Sonny was a kid...

173
00:14:33,123 --> 00:14:35,626 
he found Tom Hagen in the street,
and he had no home.

174
00:14:36,502 --> 00:14:39,004 
And so my father took him in...

175
00:14:39,588 --> 00:14:42,090 
and he's been with us ever since.

176
00:14:42,799 --> 00:14:45,302 
He's a good lawyer.

177
00:14:45,719 --> 00:14:48,096 
Not a Sicilian, but...

178
00:14:48,096 --> 00:14:50,432 
I think he's gonna be consigliere.

179
00:14:50,432 --> 00:14:52,935 
- What's that?
- That's...

180
00:14:53,519 --> 00:14:55,187 
like a counselor, an advisor.

181
00:14:55,187 --> 00:14:57,689 
Very important to the family.

182
00:14:58,273 --> 00:15:00,776 
You like your lasagna?

183
00:15:04,738 --> 00:15:09,701 
Don Corleone,
I am honored and grateful...

184
00:15:09,785 --> 00:15:12,996 
that you have invited me
to your daughter's wedding...

185
00:15:18,627 --> 00:15:21,129 
on the day
of your daughter's wedding.

186
00:15:22,047 --> 00:15:24,883 
And I hope
that their first child...

187
00:15:25,008 --> 00:15:27,511 
be a masculine child.

188
00:15:28,345 --> 00:15:33,350 
I pledge my ever-ending loyalty.

189
00:15:35,227 --> 00:15:37,229 
For your daughter's
bridal purse.

190
00:15:37,229 --> 00:15:40,232 
Thank you, Luca,
my most valued friend.

191
00:15:40,357 --> 00:15:43,819 
Don Corleone,
I'm gonna leave you now...

192
00:15:43,902 --> 00:15:45,988 
because I know you are busy.

193
00:15:45,988 --> 00:15:48,490 
Thank you.

194
00:17:52,197 --> 00:17:54,992 
Senator Cauly apologized
for not coming personally...

195
00:17:55,075 --> 00:17:57,578 
but said you'd understand.

196
00:17:57,911 --> 00:18:00,414 
Also some of the judges.

197
00:18:00,914 --> 00:18:04,418 
They've all sent gifts.
Salute!

198
00:18:05,252 --> 00:18:07,754 
What is that outside?

199
00:18:15,721 --> 00:18:18,390 
Johnny!

200
00:18:21,351 --> 00:18:23,854 
I love you.

201
00:18:29,902 --> 00:18:32,529 
Hey, Johnny, look over here!

202
00:18:32,654 --> 00:18:35,365 
He came all the way from California
to come to the wedding.

203
00:18:35,490 --> 00:18:37,576 
- I told you he was going to come.
- It's been two years.

204
00:18:37,576 --> 00:18:40,078 
- He's probably in trouble again.
- He's a good godson.

205
00:18:44,333 --> 00:18:46,835 
Sing a song.

206
00:19:01,016 --> 00:19:03,894 
Michael, you never told me
you knew Johnny Fontane.

207
00:19:03,977 --> 00:19:07,940 
- Sure. You wanna meet him?
- Huh? Oh, well, sure.

208
00:19:08,065 --> 00:19:10,108 
My father helped him
with his career.

209
00:19:10,108 --> 00:19:13,237 
- For my Connie.
- He did? How?

210
00:19:13,320 --> 00:19:15,113 
<i>I have but one</i>

211
00:19:15,113 --> 00:19:17,032 
- Let's listen to the song.
- No, Michael

212
00:19:17,115 --> 00:19:18,659 
<i>Heart</i>

213
00:19:18,659 --> 00:19:22,371 
<i>This heart I bring you</i>

214
00:19:23,956 --> 00:19:28,293 
<i>I have but one heart</i>

215
00:19:28,418 --> 00:19:30,921 
<i>To share with you</i>

216
00:19:33,382 --> 00:19:37,636 
<i>I have but one dream</i>

217
00:19:37,761 --> 00:19:41,348 
<i>That I can cling to</i>

218
00:19:42,808 --> 00:19:47,521 
<i>You are the one dream</i>

219
00:19:47,646 --> 00:19:50,899 
<i>I pray comes true</i>

220
00:19:51,817 --> 00:19:54,027 
Please, Michael. Tell me.

221
00:19:54,027 --> 00:19:57,698 
<i>My darling, until I saw you</i>

222
00:19:57,823 --> 00:19:59,825 
Well, when Johnny was first starting out...

223
00:19:59,825 --> 00:20:02,661 
he was signed to this
personal service contract...

224
00:20:02,786 --> 00:20:05,289 
with a big bandleader.

225
00:20:05,706 --> 00:20:07,791 
And as his career
got better and better...

226
00:20:07,791 --> 00:20:10,294 
he wanted to get out of it.

227
00:20:11,003 --> 00:20:13,672 
Now, Johnny is
my father's godson...

228
00:20:13,797 --> 00:20:16,300 
and my father went
to see this bandleader...

229
00:20:17,217 --> 00:20:19,720 
and he offered him
$10,000 to let Johnny go.

230
00:20:21,180 --> 00:20:23,682 
But the bandleader said no.

231
00:20:24,099 --> 00:20:27,144 
So the next day
my father went to see him...

232
00:20:27,269 --> 00:20:29,771 
only this time with Luca Brasi.

233
00:20:31,398 --> 00:20:34,484 
And within an hour,
he signed a release...

234
00:20:36,653 --> 00:20:39,281 
for a certified check of $1,000.

235
00:20:40,949 --> 00:20:42,159 
How'd he do that?

236
00:20:42,159 --> 00:20:44,661 
My father made him an offer
he couldn't refuse.

237
00:20:46,121 --> 00:20:48,624 
What was that?

238
00:20:48,749 --> 00:20:51,460 
Luca Brasi
held a gun to his head...

239
00:20:51,543 --> 00:20:53,837 
and my father assured him
that either his brains...

240
00:20:53,837 --> 00:20:56,340 
or his signature
would be on the contract.

241
00:21:01,887 --> 00:21:04,389 
That's a true story.

242
00:21:14,775 --> 00:21:17,277 
That's my family, Kay.
It's not me.

243
00:21:30,123 --> 00:21:32,626 
Beautiful!

244
00:21:40,592 --> 00:21:42,928 
My godson comes all the way
from California.

245
00:21:42,928 --> 00:21:45,430 
Give him a glass of wine.

246
00:22:04,158 --> 00:22:06,660 
I'll take care of it.

247
00:22:08,245 --> 00:22:11,123 
I want you to find Santino.
