482
00:39:16,231 --> 00:39:19,109 
from all that comedy you're
playing with that young girl.

483
00:39:19,193 --> 00:39:22,613 
Never tell anybody outside the
family what you're thinking again.

484
00:39:24,781 --> 00:39:27,284 
Go on.

485
00:39:29,995 --> 00:39:32,748 
Tom, what?
What is this nonsense?

486
00:39:32,831 --> 00:39:35,334 
It's from Johnny.
He's starring in that new film.

487
00:39:38,003 --> 00:39:39,880 
Well, take it away.

488
00:39:39,880 --> 00:39:42,382 
Take it over there.

489
00:39:42,674 --> 00:39:45,135 
And...

490
00:39:45,135 --> 00:39:47,638 
tell Luca Brasi to come in.

491
00:39:53,477 --> 00:39:56,647 
I'm a little worried
about this Sollozzo fellow.

492
00:39:56,730 --> 00:40:00,108 
I want you to find out what he's got
under his fingernails, you know?

493
00:40:00,943 --> 00:40:03,028 
Go to the Tattaglias...

494
00:40:03,028 --> 00:40:05,364 
and make them think...

495
00:40:05,364 --> 00:40:09,034 
that you're not too happy
with our family...

496
00:40:10,160 --> 00:40:12,663 
and find out what you can.

497
00:40:29,471 --> 00:40:33,433 
And I got something
for your mother and for Sonny...

498
00:40:33,559 --> 00:40:35,602 
and a tie for Freddy...

499
00:40:35,602 --> 00:40:38,313 
and Tom Hagen
got the Reynolds pen.

500
00:40:38,397 --> 00:40:40,524 
- What do you want for Christmas?
- Me?

501
00:40:40,524 --> 00:40:43,026 
Oh, just you.

502
00:41:13,348 --> 00:41:15,350 
Andiamo, Fredo.

503
00:41:15,350 --> 00:41:17,352 
Tell Paulie to get the car.
We're going.

504
00:41:17,352 --> 00:41:18,770 
Okay, Pa.

505
00:41:18,770 --> 00:41:21,690 
I'll have to get it myself, Pa.
Paulie called in sick this morning.

506
00:41:24,693 --> 00:41:27,196 
Paulie's a good kid.
I don't mind gettin' the car.

507
00:41:31,700 --> 00:41:33,202 
Buon nateli, Dano. Grazie

508
00:42:16,245 --> 00:42:19,706 
Luca, I'm Bruno Tattaglia.

509
00:42:19,832 --> 00:42:21,291 
I know.

510
00:42:21,291 --> 00:42:23,794 
Su bequero Scotch? Pre-war...

511
00:42:24,294 --> 00:42:25,796 
Io no bib' "I don't drink".

512
00:42:29,967 --> 00:42:31,468 
You know who I am?

513
00:42:31,969 --> 00:42:32,469 
I know you.

514
00:42:32,970 --> 00:42:43,438 
You have been talking to the Tattaglia
family... right? I think you and I can do
business.

515
00:42:43,939 --> 00:42:56,451 
I need someone strong like you.
I heard you are not happy with the
Corleone family. Want to join me?.

516
00:42:56,952 --> 00:42:58,954 
What's in it for me?.

517
00:43:00,038 --> 00:43:03,167 
$50,000...to start with..

518
00:43:07,045 --> 00:43:08,172 
Not bad.

519
00:43:09,965 --> 00:43:11,175 
Agreed?

520
00:43:28,942 --> 00:43:30,152 
Grazie.

521
00:44:10,609 --> 00:44:12,611 
Oh. Tom Hagen.

522
00:44:12,611 --> 00:44:14,404 
- Merry Christmas.
- Yeah.

523
00:44:14,404 --> 00:44:17,324 
I'm glad I run into you.
I wanna talk to you.

524
00:44:17,449 --> 00:44:19,326 
I haven't got time.

525
00:44:19,326 --> 00:44:22,079 
Oh, make time, consigliere.
Get in the car.

526
00:44:24,206 --> 00:44:25,791 
What are you worried about?

527
00:44:25,791 --> 00:44:28,293 
If I wanted to kill you,
you'd be dead already.

528
00:44:29,127 --> 00:44:31,630 
Get in.

529
00:44:41,807 --> 00:44:43,308 
<i>Wait a moment, Fredo.</i>

530
00:44:43,308 --> 00:44:46,311 
- I'm gonna buy some fruit.
- Okay, Pa.

531
00:44:51,441 --> 00:44:53,318 
Hi. Merry Christmas.

532
00:44:53,318 --> 00:44:55,821 
I want some fruit over there.

533
00:44:58,574 --> 00:45:01,076 
Gimme three of them.

534
00:45:02,161 --> 00:45:04,663 
No, that one.

535
00:45:22,806 --> 00:45:25,309 
Fredo!

536
00:46:11,939 --> 00:46:14,441 
Papa.

537
00:46:14,483 --> 00:46:16,985 
Papa!

538
00:46:21,824 --> 00:46:24,576 
Mike, would you like me better
if I were a nun...

539
00:46:24,701 --> 00:46:27,204 
like in the story, you know?

540
00:46:29,414 --> 00:46:30,415 
No.

541
00:46:30,541 --> 00:46:33,418 
Well, then would you like me better
if I were Ingrid Bergman?

542
00:46:33,544 --> 00:46:36,046 
Now that's a thought.

543
00:46:37,422 --> 00:46:38,423 
Michael.

544
00:46:39,091 --> 00:46:42,344 
No, I would not like you better
if you were Ingrid Bergman.

545
00:46:42,427 --> 00:46:44,930 
- Michael.
- What's the matter?

546
00:47:00,737 --> 00:47:03,240 
They don't say
if he's dead or alive.

547
00:47:25,429 --> 00:47:27,347 
Sonny, Michael.

548
00:47:27,347 --> 00:47:28,765 
<i>Michael, where you been?</i>

549
00:47:28,849 --> 00:47:30,517 
Is he all right?

550
00:47:30,517 --> 00:47:33,270 
<i>We don't know yet.</i>
There's all kinds of stories.

551
00:47:34,813 --> 00:47:37,316 
<i>He was hit bad, Mikey.</i>

552
00:47:37,733 --> 00:47:40,861 
<i>- Are you there?</i>
- Yeah, I'm here.

553
00:47:40,986 --> 00:47:43,405 
<i>Where you been? I was worried.</i>

554
00:47:43,405 --> 00:47:45,574 
Didn't Tom tell you?
I called.

555
00:47:45,574 --> 00:47:49,286 
<i>No. Look, come home, kid.</i>
You should be with Mama, you hear?

556
00:47:49,411 --> 00:47:51,914 
All right.

557
00:47:57,628 --> 00:48:00,130 
Oh, my God.

558
00:48:14,102 --> 00:48:16,605 
Who is it?

559
00:48:16,688 --> 00:48:19,191 
Open up. It's Clemenza.

560
00:48:20,192 --> 00:48:21,276 
What?

561
00:48:21,276 --> 00:48:23,779 
There's more news about your old man.

562
00:48:24,238 --> 00:48:26,323 
The word is out on the street
he's already dead.

563
00:48:26,323 --> 00:48:28,325 
Shut your mouth.
What's the matter with you?

564
00:48:28,325 --> 00:48:30,828 
Jesus Christ!
Take it easy. Take it easy.

565
00:48:30,869 --> 00:48:33,038 
- Where was Paulie?
- Paulie was out sick.

566
00:48:33,038 --> 00:48:35,582 
- He's been home sick all winter.
- How many times he been sick?

567
00:48:35,624 --> 00:48:37,209 
Only maybe three, four times.

568
00:48:37,209 --> 00:48:39,253 
I mean, I asked Freddy if he wants
a different bodyguard.

569
00:48:39,253 --> 00:48:41,004 
- He said no.
- Pick him up right now.

570
00:48:41,004 --> 00:48:42,840 
I don't care how sick he is. If he's breathin',...

571
00:48:42,840 --> 00:48:45,509 
I want you to bring him to
my father's house now. You understand? Now

572
00:48:45,592 --> 00:48:48,387 
Yeah. You want me to send any people over
here? - No, just you and him. Go ahead.

573
00:48:48,512 --> 00:48:51,014 
All right.

574
00:48:56,019 --> 00:49:01,233 
Look, uh... I'm havin' a couple of our people come
over to the house. A couple of our people.

575
00:49:04,820 --> 00:49:07,072 
<i>- Hello?</i>
- Santino Corleone?

576
00:49:07,072 --> 00:49:09,575 
<i>- Yeah.</i>
- We have Tom Hagen.

577
00:49:10,242 --> 00:49:13,704 
<i>In about three hours, he'll be</i>
released with our proposition.

578
00:49:13,787 --> 00:49:17,166 
<i>Listen to everything he has</i>
to say before you do anything.

579
00:49:17,249 --> 00:49:18,917 
<i>What's done is done.</i>

580
00:49:18,917 --> 00:49:21,879 
<i>And don't lose that famous temper</i>
of yours, huh, Sonny?

581
00:49:21,962 --> 00:49:24,464 
No, I'll wait.

582
00:49:37,978 --> 00:49:40,481 
Your boss is dead.

583
00:49:42,816 --> 00:49:45,277 
I know you're not in the muscle
end of the family, Tom...

584
00:49:45,277 --> 00:49:47,779 
so I don't want you to be scared.

585
00:49:48,363 --> 00:49:50,908 
I want you
to help the Corleones...

586
00:49:50,991 --> 00:49:53,494 
and I want you to help me.

587
00:49:56,079 --> 00:49:57,915 
Yeah. We got him outside his office...

588
00:49:57,915 --> 00:50:00,417 
just about an hour after we picked you up.

589
00:50:02,252 --> 00:50:04,755 
Drink it.

590
00:50:07,883 --> 00:50:11,303 
So now it's up to you to make
the peace between me and Sonny.

591
00:50:15,849 --> 00:50:18,352 
Sonny was hot
for my deal, wasn't he?

592
00:50:19,770 --> 00:50:22,272 
And you knew it was
the right thing to do.

593
00:50:24,107 --> 00:50:26,610 
Sonny will come after you
with everything he's got.

594
00:50:27,361 --> 00:50:29,863 
That'll be his first reaction, sure.

595
00:50:30,656 --> 00:50:33,033 
That's why you gotta
talk some sense into him.

596
00:50:33,033 --> 00:50:36,286 
The Tattaglia family is behind me
with all their people.

597
00:50:37,246 --> 00:50:39,414 
The other New York families
will go along with anything...

598
00:50:39,414 --> 00:50:41,917 
that will prevent a full-scale war.

599
00:50:42,501 --> 00:50:44,837 
Let's face it, Tom,
in all due respect...

600
00:50:44,837 --> 00:50:47,422 
the Don, rest in peace, was slippin'.

601
00:50:50,342 --> 00:50:52,845 
Ten years ago,
could I have gotten to him?

602
00:50:57,307 --> 00:50:58,851 
Well, now he's dead.

603
00:50:58,851 --> 00:51:01,353 
He's dead, Tom,
and nothing can bring him back.

604
00:51:03,021 --> 00:51:05,149 
So you gotta talk to Sonny.

605
00:51:05,149 --> 00:51:07,067 
You gotta talk
to the caporegimes...

606
00:51:07,067 --> 00:51:09,570 
that Tessio, and that fat Clemenza.

607
00:51:13,991 --> 00:51:16,493 
It's good business, Tom.

608
00:51:17,411 --> 00:51:19,705 
I'll try.

609
00:51:19,705 --> 00:51:22,374 
But even Sonny won't be able
to call off Luca Brasi.

610
00:51:25,377 --> 00:51:27,880 
Yeah. Well...

611
00:51:28,714 --> 00:51:31,216 
Let me worry about Luca.

612
00:51:36,597 --> 00:51:38,515 
You just talk to Sonny.

613
00:51:38,515 --> 00:51:41,018 
And the other two kids.

614
00:51:44,229 --> 00:51:45,731 
I'll do my best.

615
00:51:45,731 --> 00:51:48,233 
Good.

616
00:51:49,067 --> 00:51:51,570 
Now, you can go.

617
00:51:58,410 --> 00:52:01,747 
I don't like violence, Tom.
I'm a businessman.

618
00:52:03,290 --> 00:52:05,792 
Blood is a big expense.

619
00:52:26,897 --> 00:52:28,774 
He's still alive.

620
00:52:28,774 --> 00:52:31,276 
They hit him with five shots,
and he's still alive!

621
00:52:32,778 --> 00:52:34,780 
Well, that's bad luck for me...

622
00:52:34,780 --> 00:52:37,282 
and bad luck for you
if you don't make that deal.

623
00:53:22,286 --> 00:53:24,329 
Your mother's over
in the hospital with your father.

624
00:53:24,329 --> 00:53:26,832 
Looks like he's gonna
pull through, thank God.

625
00:53:28,917 --> 00:53:31,170 
- That's a lot of bad blood.
- What do you think?

626
00:53:31,170 --> 00:53:34,047 
It's too far.
I think it's too personal.

627
00:53:34,173 --> 00:53:36,800 
- The Don will consider this over.
- You gonna kill all those guys?

628
00:53:36,925 --> 00:53:39,428 
- Hey, stay out of it, Mickey, do me a favor.
- Sollozzo's the key.

629
00:53:39,428 --> 00:53:41,722 
You get rid of him,
everything falls into line.

630
00:53:41,722 --> 00:53:44,308 
What about Luca? Sollozzo
didn't seem worried about Luca.

631
00:53:46,018 --> 00:53:49,813 
I don't know. If Luca sold out,
we're in a lot of trouble.

632
00:53:49,897 --> 00:53:51,982 
Has anyone been able
to get in touch with Luca?

633
00:53:51,982 --> 00:53:54,067 
We've been tryin' all night.
He might be shacked up.

634
00:53:54,067 --> 00:53:55,152 
Hey, Mick, try him again.

635
00:53:55,152 --> 00:53:56,820 
Luca never sleeps over
with a broad.

636
00:53:56,820 --> 00:53:59,323 
He always goes home
when he's through.

637
00:53:59,865 --> 00:54:02,826 
Well, Tom, you're consigliere.

638
00:54:02,910 --> 00:54:06,038 
What do we do
if the old man dies, God forbid?

639
00:54:06,163 --> 00:54:08,665 
If we lose the old man...

640
00:54:09,416 --> 00:54:12,377 
we lose our political contacts
and half our strength.

641
00:54:12,461 --> 00:54:15,380 
The other New York families might
wind up supporting Sollozzo...

642
00:54:15,464 --> 00:54:17,841 
just to avoid a long destructive war.

643
00:54:17,841 --> 00:54:21,553 
This is almost 1946.
Nobody wants bloodshed anymore.

644
00:54:22,804 --> 00:54:25,307 
If your father dies...

645
00:54:26,642 --> 00:54:28,393 
you'll make the deal, Sonny.

646
00:54:28,393 --> 00:54:30,979 
You know, that's easy for you to say,
Tom. He's not your father.

647
00:54:31,063 --> 00:54:33,565 
I was as much a son to him
as you or Mike.

648
00:54:38,028 --> 00:54:40,531 
What is it?

649
00:54:40,531 --> 00:54:42,991 
Hey, Paulie, I thought
I told you to stay put.

650
00:54:42,991 --> 00:54:45,619 
Well, the guy at the gates,
they say they got a package.

651
00:54:45,744 --> 00:54:48,247 
Yeah?
Tessio, go see what it is.

652
00:54:51,583 --> 00:54:53,585 
- You want me to hang around?
- Yeah, hang around.

653
00:54:53,585 --> 00:54:55,087 
- You all right?
- Yeah, I'm fine.

654
00:54:55,087 --> 00:54:57,798 
Yeah? There's some food
in the icebox. You hungry or anything?

655
00:54:57,923 --> 00:54:59,967 
- No, it's all right. Thanks.
- How 'bout a drink? How 'bout a little brandy?

656
00:54:59,967 --> 00:55:01,760 
- That's good to sweat it out.
- All right, sure.

657
00:55:01,760 --> 00:55:04,263 
- Go ahead.
- That might be a good idea. Yeah, right.

658
00:55:05,931 --> 00:55:08,433 
I want you to take care
of that son of a bitch right away.

659
00:55:08,475 --> 00:55:11,019 
Paulie sold out the old man, that strutz.

660
00:55:11,103 --> 00:55:14,231 
I don't wanna see him again. Make that
first thing on your list, understand?

661
00:55:14,314 --> 00:55:15,649 
Understood.

662
00:55:15,649 --> 00:55:17,985 
Hey, Mickey, tomorrow.
You get a couple of guys.

663
00:55:17,985 --> 00:55:20,195 
You go over to Luca's apartment. Hang
around. Wait for him to show up.

664
00:55:20,195 --> 00:55:24,241 
Maybe we shouldn't get Mike
mixed up in this too directly.

665
00:55:24,366 --> 00:55:26,618 
Yeah.

666
00:55:26,618 --> 00:55:30,164 
Listen, hang around the house
on the phone. It'll be a big help.

667
00:55:31,290 --> 00:55:33,792 
Try Luca again. Go ahead.

668
00:55:42,134 --> 00:55:44,928 
- What the hell is this?
- It's a Sicilian message.

669
00:55:45,053 --> 00:55:47,556 
It means Luca Brasi sleeps with the fishes.

670
00:56:01,320 --> 00:56:03,822 
- I'm goin' now.
- What time you gonna be home tonight?

671
00:56:03,864 --> 00:56:06,366 
I don't know. Probably late.

672
00:56:07,659 --> 00:56:11,163 
- Don't forget the cannoli.
- Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

673
00:56:13,874 --> 00:56:17,669 
Rocco, sit on the other side.
You block the rearview mirror.

674
00:56:19,838 --> 00:56:21,423 
That Sonny's runnin' wild.

675
00:56:21,423 --> 00:56:23,509 
He's thinkin' of goin'
to the mattresses already.

676
00:56:23,509 --> 00:56:26,053 
We gotta find a spot
over on the West Side.

677
00:56:26,178 --> 00:56:29,264 
We'll try 309 West 43rd Street.

678
00:56:29,348 --> 00:56:31,725 
You know any good spots
on the West Side?

679
00:56:31,725 --> 00:56:34,228 
- Yeah, I'll think about it.
- Well, think about it while you're drivin'.

680
00:56:34,269 --> 00:56:36,605 
I wanna hit New York sometime this month.

681
00:56:36,605 --> 00:56:39,107 
And watch out for the kids
when you're backin' out.

682
00:56:49,493 --> 00:56:51,912 
Hey, Paulie, I want you to go
down 39th Street. Colosanto's.

683
00:56:51,912 --> 00:56:54,998 
You pick up 18 mattresses for the guys
to sleep, will you? Bring me the bill.

684
00:56:55,082 --> 00:56:58,001 
- Yeah, all right.I must go look at the bills.
No, make sure they're clean because...

685
00:56:58,085 --> 00:57:01,296 
Those guys are gonna be stuck up
in there for a long time, you know?

686
00:57:01,380 --> 00:57:03,590 
They're clean. They told me
they exterminate them.

687
00:57:03,590 --> 00:57:05,717 
"Exterminate"?
That's a bad word to use.

688
00:57:05,717 --> 00:57:08,679 
Exterminate. Get this guy.
See how we don't exterminate you.

689
00:57:08,762 --> 00:57:11,974 
<i>- Youse funny, or what?</i>
- Hey, Paulie. Did you fart?

690
00:57:12,474 --> 00:57:14,977 
- Yeah, Rocco, what'd you do?
- No, me. Nothin'. It wasn't me.

691
00:57:15,060 --> 00:57:17,104 
- It's gotta be him.
- Hey, pull over, will you.

692
00:57:17,104 --> 00:57:19,606 
I gotta take a leak.

693
00:58:00,814 --> 00:58:02,608 
Leave the gun.

694
00:58:02,608 --> 00:58:05,110 
Take the cannoli.

695
00:58:21,919 --> 00:58:23,420 
<i>Hey, Mike?</i>

696
00:58:23,921 --> 00:58:25,422 
<i>Hey, Mikey?</i>

697
00:58:26,924 --> 00:58:27,925 
Yeah?

698
00:58:28,008 --> 00:58:29,426 
<i>You're wanted on the telephone.</i>

699
00:58:35,140 --> 00:58:37,643 
- Who is it?
- It's some girl.

700
00:58:41,688 --> 00:58:42,898 
Hello, Kay?

701
00:58:42,898 --> 00:58:44,274 
<i>How's your father?</i>

702
00:58:44,274 --> 00:58:46,068 
He's good.
He's gonna make it.

703
00:58:46,068 --> 00:58:48,570 
<i>I love you.</i>

704
00:58:48,570 --> 00:58:49,571 
Huh?

705
00:58:49,863 --> 00:58:51,865 
<i>I love you!</i>

706
00:58:52,115 --> 00:58:53,617 
<i>Michael?</i>

707
00:58:53,992 --> 00:58:54,993 
Yeah, I know.

708
00:58:54,993 --> 00:58:56,829 
<i>Tell me you love me.</i>

709
00:58:56,829 --> 00:58:58,497 
Yeah, I can't talk.

710
00:58:58,497 --> 00:59:00,290 
<i>Can't you say it?</i>

711
00:59:01,124 --> 00:59:03,627 
Yeah, I'll see you tonight.

712
00:59:03,836 --> 00:59:06,797 
Hey, Mikey. Why don't you tell
that nice girl you love her?

713
00:59:06,922 --> 00:59:09,007 
I love you with all-a my heart!

714
00:59:09,007 --> 00:59:11,510 
If I don't see you again a-soon,
I'm-a gonna die!

715
00:59:12,761 --> 00:59:14,763 
Come over here, kid.
Learn somethin'.

716
00:59:14,763 --> 00:59:17,266 
You never know. You might have to cook
for 20 guys someday.

717
00:59:17,766 --> 00:59:20,102 
You see? You start out
with a little bit of oil.

718
00:59:20,102 --> 00:59:21,687 
Then you fry some garlic.

719
00:59:21,687 --> 00:59:24,314 
Then you throw in some tomatoes,
some tomato paste.

720
00:59:24,398 --> 00:59:27,067 
You fry it.
You make sure it doesn't stick.

721
00:59:27,192 --> 00:59:30,320 
When you got it to a boil, you shove in
all your sausage and your meatballs.

722
00:59:33,198 --> 00:59:35,701 
Add a little bit of wine.

723
00:59:38,537 --> 00:59:41,456 
And a little bit of sugar.

724
00:59:42,207 --> 00:59:44,209 
- And that's my trick.
- Why don't you cut the crap?

725
00:59:44,209 --> 00:59:46,378 
I got more important things
for you to do.

726
00:59:46,378 --> 00:59:49,006 
- How's Paulie?
- Oh, Paulie. Won't see him no more.

727
00:59:51,049 --> 00:59:53,552 
- Where you going?
- To the city.

728
00:59:53,552 --> 00:59:55,220 
Send some bodyguards with him.

729
00:59:55,220 --> 00:59:57,222 
- No. I'm just going to the hospital to see Pop.
- Nevermind. Send somebody with him.

730
00:59:57,222 --> 01:00:00,142 
Oh, he'll be all right.
Sollozzo knows he's a civilian.

731
01:00:00,225 --> 01:00:02,728 
- All right. Be careful, huh?
- Yes, sir.

732
01:00:05,731 --> 01:00:08,233 
Send somebody with him anyway.

733
01:00:36,428 --> 01:00:38,263 
I have to go.

734
01:00:38,263 --> 01:00:40,766 
Can I go with you?

735
01:00:41,099 --> 01:00:43,685 
No, Kay. There's gonna be
detectives there.

736
01:00:43,769 --> 01:00:45,771 
People from the press.

737
01:00:45,771 --> 01:00:48,273 
Well, I'll ride in a cab.

738
01:00:50,275 --> 01:00:52,778 
I don't want you to get involved.

739
01:00:55,447 --> 01:00:57,950 
When will I see you again?

740
01:01:04,122 --> 01:01:06,124 
Go back to New Hampshire...

741
01:01:06,124 --> 01:01:08,627 
and I'll call you
at your parents' house.

742
01:01:09,962 --> 01:01:12,464 
When will I see you again,
Michael?

743
01:01:13,966 --> 01:01:16,468 
I don't know.

744
01:03:26,515 --> 01:03:28,642 
What are you doing here?

745
01:03:28,642 --> 01:03:30,769 
You're not supposed
to be here now.

746
01:03:30,769 --> 01:03:34,314 
I'm Michael Corleone.
This is my father.

747
01:03:34,439 --> 01:03:36,984 
There's nobody here.
What happened to the guards?

748
01:03:37,109 --> 01:03:39,444 
Your father just had
too many visitors.

749
01:03:39,444 --> 01:03:42,322 
They interfered
with hospital service.

750
01:03:42,447 --> 01:03:45,325 
The police made them leave
about ten minutes ago.

751
01:03:50,289 --> 01:03:54,168 
Get me Long Beach 4-5-6-2-0, please.

752
01:03:56,795 --> 01:03:59,298 
Nurse, wait a minute.
Stay here.

753
01:04:03,135 --> 01:04:05,470 
Sonny, Michael.
I'm at the hospital.

754
01:04:05,470 --> 01:04:08,015 
Listen. I got here late.
There's nobody here.

755
01:04:08,140 --> 01:04:11,101 
Nobody. No Tessio's men,
no detectives, nobody.

756
01:04:11,226 --> 01:04:14,021 
<i>- Pop is all alone.</i>
- Don't panic. We'll send somebody.

757
01:04:14,146 --> 01:04:16,482 
I won't panic.

758
01:04:16,482 --> 01:04:19,026 
I'm sorry, but you will
have to leave.

759
01:04:21,987 --> 01:04:24,698 
You and I are gonna move my father
to another room.

760
01:04:24,823 --> 01:04:27,868 
Now, can you disconnect those tubes
so we can move the bed out?

761
01:04:27,993 --> 01:04:31,455 
- That's out of the question.
- Do you know my father?

762
01:04:31,580 --> 01:04:33,790 
Men are coming here to kill him.

763
01:04:33,790 --> 01:04:35,918 
You understand?

764
01:04:35,918 --> 01:04:38,420 
Now, help me, please.

765
01:05:54,746 --> 01:05:59,501 
- Who are you?
- I am Enzo... the baker.

766
01:05:59,585 --> 01:06:01,086 
- You remember me?
- Enzo?

767
01:06:01,086 --> 01:06:02,921 
- Yes, Enzo.
- You better get out of here, Enzo.

768
01:06:02,921 --> 01:06:04,923 
There's gonna be trouble.

769
01:06:04,923 --> 01:06:07,426 
If there is trouble,
I stay here to help you...

770
01:06:07,426 --> 01:06:09,928 
For your father. For your father.

771
01:06:10,929 --> 01:06:12,764 
All right, listen.

772
01:06:12,764 --> 01:06:14,933 
Wait for me outside,
in front of the hospital.

773
01:06:14,933 --> 01:06:17,978 
All right? I'll be out
in a minute. Go ahead.

774
01:06:17,978 --> 01:06:19,354 
Okay, okay.

775
01:06:31,909 --> 01:06:36,205 
Just lie here, Pop.
I'll take care of you now.

776
01:06:37,414 --> 01:06:39,917 
I'm with you now.

777
01:06:41,084 --> 01:06:43,587 
I'm with you.

778
01:07:18,121 --> 01:07:20,624 
Get rid of these.
Come here.

779
01:07:20,958 --> 01:07:23,460 
Put your hand in your pocket
like you have a gun.

780
01:07:24,127 --> 01:07:26,630 
You'll be all right.

781
01:07:30,884 --> 01:07:33,387 
You'll be okay.

782
01:08:17,097 --> 01:08:19,600 
You did good.

783
01:08:52,758 --> 01:08:54,927 
Here he is.

784
01:08:54,927 --> 01:08:57,387 
All right, hold still.

785
01:09:06,939 --> 01:09:09,274 
I thought I got
all you guinea hoods locked up.

786
01:09:09,274 --> 01:09:10,776 
What the hell are you doing here?

787
01:09:10,776 --> 01:09:13,237 
What happened to the men who
were guarding my father, Captain?

788
01:09:13,612 --> 01:09:15,280 
Why, you little punk.

789
01:09:15,280 --> 01:09:17,282 
What the hell are you doing,
telling me my business?

790
01:09:17,282 --> 01:09:19,159 
I pulled them guys off of here.

791
01:09:19,159 --> 01:09:22,162 
Now, you get out of here
and stay away from this hospital.

792
01:09:22,287 --> 01:09:25,249 
I'm not moving until you put
some guards around my father's room.

793
01:09:25,958 --> 01:09:27,960 
Phil, take him in.

794
01:09:27,960 --> 01:09:30,379 
The kid's clean, Captain.
He's a war hero.

795
01:09:30,379 --> 01:09:33,298 
- He's never been busted...
- Goddamn it, I said take him in.

796
01:09:35,384 --> 01:09:37,886 
What's the Turk paying you
to set up my father, Captain?

797
01:09:39,221 --> 01:09:41,348 
Take a hold of him.
Stand him up.

798
01:09:41,348 --> 01:09:43,851 
Stand him up straight.

799
01:10:05,747 --> 01:10:07,833 
I'm the attorney
for the Corleone family.

800
01:10:07,833 --> 01:10:10,544 
These men are private detectives
hired to protect Vito Corleone.

801
01:10:11,420 --> 01:10:13,172 
They're licensed to carry firearms.

802
01:10:13,172 --> 01:10:15,674 
If you interfere, you'll have to
appear before a judge...

803
01:10:15,757 --> 01:10:18,302 
in the morning and show cause.

804
01:10:18,427 --> 01:10:20,929 
All right, let him go.

805
01:10:21,013 --> 01:10:23,474 
Come on.

806
01:10:52,961 --> 01:10:54,963 
What's with all the new faces?

807
01:10:54,963 --> 01:10:56,798 
Gonna need 'em now.

808
01:10:56,798 --> 01:10:59,426 
After the hospital thing,
Sonny got mad.

809
01:10:59,551 --> 01:11:02,679 
We hit Bruno Tattaglia
at 4:00 this morning.

810
01:11:03,972 --> 01:11:06,475 
Jesus Christ.

811
01:11:12,815 --> 01:11:15,317 
Looks like a fortress around here.

812
01:11:17,820 --> 01:11:18,904 
Tom-anuch!

813
01:11:19,822 --> 01:11:22,699 
A hundred button men on the street,
24 hours a day.

814
01:11:22,825 --> 01:11:26,036 
That Turk shows one hair
on his ass, he's dead. Believe me.

815
01:11:28,664 --> 01:11:31,166 
Hey, Mike, come here.
Let me look at you.

816
01:11:34,586 --> 01:11:36,296 
You look beautiful.
Just beautiful.

817
01:11:36,296 --> 01:11:37,798 
You're gorgeous.

818
01:11:37,798 --> 01:11:40,509 
Hey, listen to this.
The Turk, he wants to talk.

819
01:11:40,592 --> 01:11:43,345 
Eh gosh...Imagine the nerve
on this son of a bitch.

820
01:11:43,428 --> 01:11:45,764 
Craps out last night,
he wants a meeting today.

821
01:11:45,764 --> 01:11:48,267 
- What'd he say?
- What did he say?

822
01:11:48,934 --> 01:11:51,103 
He wants us to send Michael
to hear the proposition.

823
01:11:51,103 --> 01:11:54,189 
And the promise is that the deal
is so good that we can't refuse.

824
01:11:54,773 --> 01:11:56,441 
What about Bruno Tattaglia?

825
01:11:56,441 --> 01:11:58,110 
That's part of the deal.

826
01:11:58,110 --> 01:12:00,112 
Bruno cancels out what they did
to my father.

827
01:12:00,112 --> 01:12:02,614 
Sonny, we ought to hear
what they have to say.

828
01:12:02,948 --> 01:12:05,450 
No. No. No. No more.
Not this time, Consigliere.

829
01:12:05,450 --> 01:12:09,037 
No more meetings, no more discussions,
no more Sollozzo tricks.

830
01:12:09,121 --> 01:12:10,956 
You give them one message...
I want Sollozzo.

831
01:12:10,956 --> 01:12:12,624 
If not, it's all-out war.
We go to the mattresses.

832
01:12:12,624 --> 01:12:14,293 
Some of the other families
won't sit still for a war.

833
01:12:14,293 --> 01:12:16,461 
- Then they hand me Sollozzo.
- Your father wouldn't hear this.

834
01:12:16,461 --> 01:12:19,548 
- This is business, not personal.
- They shot my father...Your ass...

835
01:12:19,631 --> 01:12:23,051 
Even shooting your father
was business, not personal, Sonny.

836
01:12:23,135 --> 01:12:24,970 
Well, then business will have to suffer.
All right?

837
01:12:24,970 --> 01:12:26,805 
And listen... do me a favor, Tom...

838
01:12:26,805 --> 01:12:28,807 
No more advice on how
to patch things up.

839
01:12:28,807 --> 01:12:31,310 
Just help me win, please.
All right?

840
01:12:37,274 --> 01:12:39,818 
I found out about this Captain McCluskey
who broke Mike's jaw.

841
01:12:39,943 --> 01:12:41,445 
What about him?

842
01:12:41,445 --> 01:12:44,490 
Now he's definitely on Sollozzo's
payroll, and for big money.

843
01:12:44,615 --> 01:12:47,493 
McCluskey has agreed
to be the Turk's bodyguard.

844
01:12:47,618 --> 01:12:49,620 
What you have to understand,
Sonny...

845
01:12:49,620 --> 01:12:51,788 
is that while Sollozzo's
being guarded like this...

846
01:12:51,788 --> 01:12:53,624 
he is invulnerable.

847
01:12:53,624 --> 01:12:57,169 
Nobody has ever gunned down
a New York police captain. Never.

848
01:12:57,294 --> 01:13:00,339 
It would be disastrous. All the
five families would come after you, Sonny.

849
01:13:00,464 --> 01:13:03,175 
The Corleone family
would be outcast.

850
01:13:03,300 --> 01:13:06,970 
Even the old man's political
protection would run for cover.

851
01:13:08,472 --> 01:13:10,641 
So do me a favor.

852
01:13:10,641 --> 01:13:13,268 
Take this into consideration.

853
01:13:16,063 --> 01:13:18,565 
All right, we'll wait.

854
01:13:23,320 --> 01:13:25,823 
We can't wait.

855
01:13:25,823 --> 01:13:27,825 
Can't wait.

856
01:13:27,825 --> 01:13:29,576 
I don't care what Sollozzo says
about a deal.

857
01:13:29,576 --> 01:13:31,745 
He's gonna kill Pop.
That's it.

858
01:13:31,745 --> 01:13:33,580 
That's the key for him.

859
01:13:33,580 --> 01:13:35,582 
Got to get Sollozzo.

860
01:13:35,582 --> 01:13:37,751 
CLEMENZA: Mike is right.

861
01:13:37,751 --> 01:13:39,753 
Let me ask you something first.

862
01:13:39,753 --> 01:13:42,840 
What about this McCluskey?

863
01:13:42,923 --> 01:13:45,425 
What do we do with this cop here?

864
01:13:49,763 --> 01:13:52,266 
They want to have a meeting
with me, right?

865
01:13:53,767 --> 01:13:56,353 
It will be me...

866
01:13:56,436 --> 01:13:58,939 
McCluskey and Sollozzo.

867
01:13:59,940 --> 01:14:02,442 
Let's set the meeting.

868
01:14:04,111 --> 01:14:07,531 
Get our informers to find out
where it's going to be held.

869
01:14:09,616 --> 01:14:13,370 
Now we insist it's a public place...
a bar, a restaurant.

870
01:14:13,453 --> 01:14:17,207 
Someplace where there's people,
so I feel safe.

871
01:14:20,127 --> 01:14:23,046 
They're gonna search me
when I first meet them, right?

872
01:14:23,130 --> 01:14:25,632 
So I can't have a weapon on me then.

873
01:14:28,802 --> 01:14:31,305 
But if Clemenza can figure a way...

874
01:14:31,430 --> 01:14:33,891 
to have a weapon
planted there for me...

875
01:14:38,770 --> 01:14:41,231 
then I'll kill them both.

876
01:14:53,118 --> 01:14:55,662 
What are you gonna do?
Nice college boy, huh?

877
01:14:55,787 --> 01:14:57,789 
Didn't want to get mixed up
in the family business.

878
01:14:57,789 --> 01:14:59,791 
Now you want to gun down
a police captain?

879
01:14:59,791 --> 01:15:01,793 
Why? 'Cause he slapped you
in the face a little bit?

880
01:15:01,793 --> 01:15:04,129 
What do you think this is, the army,
where you shoot them a mile away?

881
01:15:04,129 --> 01:15:05,797 
You've gotta
get up close like this and bada-bing!

882
01:15:05,797 --> 01:15:09,176 
You blow their brains all over your
nice Ivy League suit. Come here.

883
01:15:09,301 --> 01:15:11,637 
You're taking this very personal.

884
01:15:11,637 --> 01:15:14,848 
Tom, this is business, and this man
is taking it very, very personal.

885
01:15:14,973 --> 01:15:16,975 
Where does it say that
you can't kill a cop?

886
01:15:16,975 --> 01:15:19,520 
- Come on, Mikey.
- Tom, wait a minute.

887
01:15:19,645 --> 01:15:22,356 
I'm talking about a cop
that's mixed up in drugs.

888
01:15:22,481 --> 01:15:26,610 
I'm talking about a dishonest cop,
a crooked cop...

889
01:15:26,693 --> 01:15:29,571 
who got mixed up in the rackets
and got what was coming to him.

890
01:15:29,655 --> 01:15:31,740 
That's a terrific story.

891
01:15:31,740 --> 01:15:34,451 
Now we have newspaper people
on the payroll, don't we, Tom?

892
01:15:35,994 --> 01:15:38,247 
They might like a story like that.

893
01:15:38,247 --> 01:15:40,749 
They might.
They just might.

894
01:15:43,585 --> 01:15:45,754 
It's not personal, Sonny.

895
01:15:45,754 --> 01:15:48,257 
It's strictly business.

896
01:15:50,259 --> 01:15:51,927 
It's as cold as they come.

897
01:15:51,927 --> 01:15:55,472 
Impossible to trace, so you don't
worry about prints, Mike.

898
01:15:55,597 --> 01:15:58,475 
I put a special tape
on the trigger and the butt.

899
01:15:58,600 --> 01:16:01,103 
Here. Try it.

900
01:16:11,780 --> 01:16:14,283 
What's the matter,
the trigger too tight?

901
01:16:17,452 --> 01:16:19,621 
- My ears.
- I left it noisy.

902
01:16:19,621 --> 01:16:24,334 
Yeah, I left it noisy  that way it scares
any pain-in-the-ass innocent bystanders
away.

903
01:16:24,459 --> 01:16:26,962 
All right, you shot them both.
Now what do you do?

904
01:16:29,548 --> 01:16:31,717 
Sit down, finish my dinner.

905
01:16:31,717 --> 01:16:33,385 
Come on, kid.
Don't fool around.

906
01:16:33,385 --> 01:16:36,972 
Just let your hand drop to your side
and let the gun slip out.

907
01:16:37,055 --> 01:16:39,224 
Everybody will still think
you got it.

908
01:16:39,224 --> 01:16:41,393 
They're gonna be staring
at your face, Mike...

909
01:16:41,393 --> 01:16:44,480 
so walk out of the place real fast,
but you don't run.

910
01:16:44,563 --> 01:16:47,983 
Don't look nobody directly in the
eye, but you don't look away, either.

911
01:16:48,066 --> 01:16:50,068 
Hey, they're gonna be scared stiff
of you, believe me...

912
01:16:50,068 --> 01:16:52,571 
so don't worry about nothing.

913
01:16:53,739 --> 01:16:55,574 
You know, you're gonna turn out all right.

914
01:16:55,574 --> 01:16:57,910 
You take a long vacation,
nobody knows where...

915
01:16:57,910 --> 01:17:00,412 
and we're gonna catch the hell.

916
01:17:00,412 --> 01:17:02,581 
How bad do you think
it's gonna be?

917
01:17:02,581 --> 01:17:04,583 
Pretty goddamn bad.

918
01:17:04,583 --> 01:17:07,669 
Probably all the other families
will line up against us.

919
01:17:07,753 --> 01:17:10,672 
That's all right. These things
gotta happen every five years or so.

920
01:17:10,756 --> 01:17:13,342 
Ten years.
Helps to get rid of the bad blood.

921
01:17:13,425 --> 01:17:16,011 
Been ten years since
the last one.

922
01:17:16,094 --> 01:17:18,096 
You know, you gotta stop them
at the beginning...

923
01:17:18,096 --> 01:17:20,265 
like they should have
stopped Hitler at Munich.

924
01:17:20,265 --> 01:17:22,267 
They should have never let him
get away with that.

925
01:17:22,267 --> 01:17:24,770 
They was just asking
for big trouble.

926
01:17:25,103 --> 01:17:27,689 
You know, Mike,
we was all proud of you...

927
01:17:27,773 --> 01:17:29,566 
being a hero and all.

928
01:17:29,566 --> 01:17:32,069 
Your father too.

929
01:18:09,439 --> 01:18:11,275 
Nothing.
Not a hint.

930
01:18:11,275 --> 01:18:13,777 
Absolutely nothing.

931
01:18:13,944 --> 01:18:16,822 
Even Sollozzo's people don't know
where the meeting's gonna be held.

932
01:18:18,115 --> 01:18:20,617 
How much time do we have?

933
01:18:21,451 --> 01:18:23,287 
They're gonna pick you up in front of Jack
Dempsey's joint...

934
01:18:23,287 --> 01:18:25,789 
in an hour and a half...
exactly an hour and a half.

935
01:18:27,457 --> 01:18:29,960 
We could put a tail on them,
see how it turns out.

936
01:18:30,043 --> 01:18:33,297 
Sollozzo'll lose our ass
going around the block.

937
01:18:33,380 --> 01:18:34,923 
What about the negotiator?

938
01:18:34,923 --> 01:18:37,634 
He's over at my place playing
pinochle with a couple of my men.

939
01:18:37,718 --> 01:18:39,511 
He's happy.
They're letting him win.

940
01:18:39,511 --> 01:18:43,140 
It's too much of a risk for Mike.
Maybe we ought to call it off, Sonny.

941
01:18:43,265 --> 01:18:46,810 
The negotiator keeps on playing cards
until Mike comes back safe and sound.

942
01:18:46,935 --> 01:18:49,229 
So why don't they just blast who's ever
