01:44:46,995 --> 01:44:49,998 
...this is my daughter, Apollonia...

1181
01:44:49,998 --> 01:44:53,001 
and this is Michael Corleone.

1182
01:45:09,017 --> 01:45:11,019 
Thank you.

1183
01:45:11,603 --> 01:45:13,605 
Your welcome.

1184
01:45:23,615 --> 01:45:26,118 
What's the problem with your eye.

1185
01:45:26,618 --> 01:45:29,121 
No, no. It's nothing. It's fine.

1186
01:46:43,821 --> 01:46:46,323 
Hey! I'm gonna knock you dizzy.

1187
01:46:51,829 --> 01:46:54,331 
Save it for the library.

1188
01:46:57,459 --> 01:46:59,962 
Come on. We gotta go
pick up my sister. Let's go.

1189
01:47:18,188 --> 01:47:20,691 
What's the matter?

1190
01:47:22,484 --> 01:47:24,486 
What's the matter?

1191
01:47:25,696 --> 01:47:27,865 
- It was my fault!
- Where is he?

1192
01:47:27,865 --> 01:47:31,243 
Sonny, please. It was my fault.
Sonny, it was my fault. I hit him.

1193
01:47:31,368 --> 01:47:33,287 
I started a fight with him.
Please, Sonny.

1194
01:47:33,287 --> 01:47:35,789 
I'm sorry.

1195
01:47:39,751 --> 01:47:43,088 
Okay, I'm just... I'm just gonna get a
doctor to come and take a look at you.

1196
01:47:43,297 --> 01:47:46,049 
Sonny, please don't do anything.
Please, don't do it.

1197
01:47:48,135 --> 01:47:50,304 
What's the matter with you?
What am I gonna do?

1198
01:47:50,304 --> 01:47:53,098 
Am I gonna make that baby an orphan
before he's born?

1199
01:47:55,976 --> 01:47:57,478 
All right?

1200
01:47:57,478 --> 01:48:00,564 
This fat slob's still bettin' the Yankees
pretty heavy?

1201
01:48:00,689 --> 01:48:03,192 
You tell 'em to stop takin'
action on 'em, alright?

1202
01:48:04,359 --> 01:48:06,862 
You lost enough money
last weekend to me.

1203
01:48:12,743 --> 01:48:15,245 
Carlo, come here.

1204
01:49:12,344 --> 01:49:15,055 
You touch my sister again,
I'll kill you.

1205
01:53:10,415 --> 01:53:13,127 
Weren't expecting you, Kay.
You should call.

1206
01:53:13,252 --> 01:53:17,548 
Yes, well, I have.
I mean I've tried writing and calling.

1207
01:53:17,631 --> 01:53:20,008 
Now, I wanna reach Michael.

1208
01:53:20,008 --> 01:53:23,428 
Nobody knows where he is. We know
that he's all right, but that's all.

1209
01:53:26,682 --> 01:53:28,684 
- What was that?
- That's an accident.

1210
01:53:28,684 --> 01:53:31,395 
But nobody was hurt.

1211
01:53:31,436 --> 01:53:32,437 
Tom...

1212
01:53:32,938 --> 01:53:36,775 
Would you give this letter
to Michael, please? Please?

1213
01:53:36,900 --> 01:53:39,236 
Well, if I accepted that...

1214
01:53:39,236 --> 01:53:42,781 
in a court of law they could prove that
I have knowledge of his whereabouts.

1215
01:53:42,906 --> 01:53:45,117 
Now you just be patient, Kay.
He'll get in touch with you, all right?

1216
01:53:45,117 --> 01:53:48,996 
I let my cab go, so can I come in
to call another one, please?

1217
01:53:49,121 --> 01:53:51,623 
Come on. I'm sorry.
Come on.

1218
01:54:07,931 --> 01:54:10,434 
Hello?

1219
01:54:11,977 --> 01:54:13,770 
<i>Is Carlo there?</i>

1220
01:54:13,770 --> 01:54:16,231 
<i>- Who's this?</i>
- This is a friend of Carlo's.

1221
01:54:16,231 --> 01:54:19,276 
<i>Would you tell him that</i>
I can't make it tonight until later?

1222
01:54:25,491 --> 01:54:27,993 
Bitch.

1223
01:54:28,786 --> 01:54:31,371 
- Dinner's on the table.
- I'm not hungry yet.

1224
01:54:31,497 --> 01:54:33,499 
Your food is on the table.
It's getting cold.

1225
01:54:33,499 --> 01:54:36,543 
- I'll eat out later.
- You just told me to make you dinner.

1226
01:54:36,668 --> 01:54:38,670 
Hey, fuck you, eh?

1227
01:54:38,670 --> 01:54:41,131 
Go fuck yourself!

1228
01:54:45,844 --> 01:54:48,347 
What the hell is she up to now, this
little guinea brat.

1229
01:54:52,768 --> 01:54:55,354 
That's it. Break it all,
you spoiled guinea brat.

1230
01:54:55,479 --> 01:54:57,981 
Break it all!

1231
01:55:00,692 --> 01:55:03,153 
That's it. Break it all.

1232
01:55:06,281 --> 01:55:10,494 
Why don't you bring
your whore home for dinner?

1233
01:55:10,577 --> 01:55:13,080 
Maybe I will.
Why not?

1234
01:55:18,752 --> 01:55:21,213 
- Now clean it up!
- Like hell I will!

1235
01:55:21,213 --> 01:55:23,715 
Clean it up! Clean it up, you guinea
spoiled brat!

1236
01:55:23,715 --> 01:55:30,222 
Clean it up! Clean it up, I
said clean it up! Clean that up! Clean it
up!

1237
01:55:30,639 --> 01:55:33,142 
You son of a bitch!

1238
01:55:33,642 --> 01:55:41,150 
Clean it up! Clean that up you son-of-a-
bitch! Clean it! Clean it up!

1239
01:55:41,817 --> 01:55:44,903 
Yeah yeah...	Come on, now! Kill me!
Be a murderer like your father!

1240
01:55:45,028 --> 01:55:47,364 
- Come on! All you Corleones are murderers!
- I hate you!

1241
01:55:47,364 --> 01:55:49,074 
- Come on!
- I'll kill you!

1242
01:55:49,074 --> 01:55:51,577 
- Come on! Kill me!
Get up!

1243
01:55:51,577 --> 01:55:53,245 
Get out of here!

1244
01:55:53,245 --> 01:55:56,707 
- I hate you!
- Now go ahead. Now I'll kill you.

1245
01:55:56,832 --> 01:55:58,834 
You guinea brat, you.

1246
01:55:58,834 --> 01:56:01,336 
Get out here!

1247
01:56:10,179 --> 01:56:13,098 
Connie, what's the matter?
I can't hear you. What is it?

1248
01:56:14,266 --> 01:56:17,144 
Honey, talk louder.
The baby's crying.

1249
01:56:17,269 --> 01:56:19,271 
Santino, I can't understand.
I don't know.

1250
01:56:19,271 --> 01:56:21,356 
I don't understand.

1251
01:56:21,356 --> 01:56:23,859 
Yeah, Connie.

1252
01:56:28,405 --> 01:56:30,908 
Listen, you wait there.

1253
01:56:32,785 --> 01:56:35,245 
No, you just wait there.

1254
01:56:37,080 --> 01:56:39,958 
- That son of a bitch.
- Sonny, what's the matter?

1255
01:56:40,083 --> 01:56:42,211 
- Son of a bitch!
- What's the matter?

1256
01:56:42,211 --> 01:56:44,713 
Damn it!

1257
01:56:46,882 --> 01:56:49,510 
Open the goddamn gate.
Get off your ass.

1258
01:57:06,026 --> 01:57:08,862 
- Sonny, come on!
- Get out of here!

1259
01:57:08,987 --> 01:57:11,448 
Go after him.
Go on.

1260
01:57:39,852 --> 01:57:41,812 
Son of a bitch.

1261
01:57:41,812 --> 01:57:44,314 
Come on! Come on!

1262
01:59:31,380 --> 01:59:33,882 
Give me a drop.

1263
01:59:41,473 --> 01:59:43,976 
My wife is crying upstairs.

1264
01:59:46,145 --> 01:59:48,647 
I hear cars coming to the house.

1265
01:59:53,235 --> 01:59:55,737 
Consigliere of mine...

1266
01:59:56,613 --> 01:59:59,533 
I think you should tell your Don
what everyone seems to know.

1267
01:59:59,658 --> 02:00:02,119 
Well, I didn't tell Mama anything.

1268
02:00:03,328 --> 02:00:06,874 
I was about to come up and wake you
just now and tell you.

1269
02:00:10,002 --> 02:00:12,504 
But you needed a drink first.

1270
02:00:19,094 --> 02:00:21,597 
Now you've had your drink.

1271
02:00:27,144 --> 02:00:31,315 
They shot Sonny on the causeway.
He's dead.

1272
02:00:48,582 --> 02:00:51,084 
I want all inquiries made.

1273
02:00:55,255 --> 02:00:57,758 
I want no acts of vengeance.

1274
02:00:59,301 --> 02:01:01,804 
I want you to arrange a meeting...

1275
02:01:03,096 --> 02:01:05,599 
with the heads
of the five families.

1276
02:01:07,851 --> 02:01:10,354 
This war stops now.

1277
02:01:31,792 --> 02:01:34,336 
Call Bonasera.

1278
02:01:34,419 --> 02:01:36,922 
We need him now.

1279
02:01:48,767 --> 02:01:51,770 
This is Tom Hagen
calling for Vito Corleone...

1280
02:01:51,854 --> 02:01:53,939 
at his request.

1281
02:01:53,939 --> 02:01:56,275 
Now, you owe your Don a service.

1282
02:01:56,275 --> 02:02:00,070 
<i>He has no doubt that</i>
you will repay it.

1283
02:02:00,195 --> 02:02:02,948 
<i>Now, he will be at your</i>
funeral parlor in one hour.

1284
02:02:03,073 --> 02:02:05,576 
<i>Be there to greet him.</i>

1285
02:02:25,804 --> 02:02:28,140 
Well, my friend...

1286
02:02:28,140 --> 02:02:30,601 
are you ready
to do me this service?

1287
02:02:30,601 --> 02:02:32,269 
Yes.

1288
02:02:32,269 --> 02:02:34,771 
What do you want me to do?

1289
02:02:42,154 --> 02:02:45,157 
I want you to use
all your powers...

1290
02:02:45,282 --> 02:02:47,785 
and all your skills.

1291
02:02:50,788 --> 02:02:53,290 
I don't want his mother
to see him this way.

1292
02:03:09,848 --> 02:03:12,309
Look how they massacred my boy.

1293
02:03:44,842 --> 02:03:45,362
It's safer to teach you English!

1294
02:03:45,843 --> 02:03:46,343
I know English...

1295
02:03:47,219 --> 02:03:49,096 
Monday, Tuesday, Thursday...

1296
02:03:49,096 --> 02:03:51,723 
Wednesday, Friday,
Sunday, Saturday.

1297
02:04:02,109 --> 02:04:03,735 
How are things in Palermo?

1298
02:04:10,117 --> 02:04:15,539 
Michael is teaching me to drive  watch,
I'll show you.

1299
02:04:19,084 --> 02:04:21,044
Young people don't respect anything
anymore. Times are changing for the worse.
This place has become too dangerous for
you. I don't think you're safe here. I
want you to move to a villa near Siracusa,
right now...Subita, eh?

1300
02:04:45,110 --> 02:04:46,528 
What's wrong?

1301
02:04:48,113 --> 02:04:56,538
Bad news from America. Your brother,
Santino, they killed him.

1302
02:05:01,084 --> 02:05:02,274
Michele...Michele, Let's go... let's go...
you promised me.

1303
02:05:24,149 --> 02:05:26,610
- Fabrizio.
- Yes, sir?

1304
02:05:27,778 --> 02:05:29,446 
Are you driving yourself, boss?

1305
02:05:29,446 --> 02:05:31,740 
- Yes.
- Is your wife coming with you?

1306
02:05:31,740 --> 02:05:35,285 
No. I want you to take her to her father's
house till I know things are safe.

1307
02:05:35,410 --> 02:05:37,913
Okay. Anything you say, boss.

1308
02:05:45,087 --> 02:05:45,897
Calo, dové Apollonia?

1309
02:05:46,088 --> 02:05:47,178
She's going to surprise you  she wants to
drive.

1310
02:05:52,094 --> 02:05:53,024
She'll make a good American wife.

1311
02:05:56,098 --> 02:05:56,988
Wait, I'll get the baggage...

1312
02:06:13,115 --> 02:06:14,125
Michele, wait there! I'll drive to you...

1313
02:06:22,082 --> 02:06:22,862
NO! No, Apollonia!

1314
02:06:46,940 --> 02:06:48,901
Don Barzini,
I want to thank you...

1315
02:06:48,901 --> 02:06:52,404 
for helping me organize
this meeting here today.

1316
02:06:52,529 --> 02:06:55,866 
And also the other heads
of the five families...

1317
02:06:55,991 --> 02:06:58,494 
from New York and New Jersey.

1318
02:06:59,495 --> 02:07:02,498 
Carmine Cuneo from the Bronx.

1319
02:07:05,000 --> 02:07:07,503 
And Brooklyn...

1320
02:07:07,669 --> 02:07:10,172 
Philip Tattaglia.

1321
02:07:11,590 --> 02:07:14,384 
And from Staten Island...

1322
02:07:14,510 --> 02:07:17,763 
we have with us Victor Strachi.

1323
02:07:17,888 --> 02:07:20,390 
And all the other associates
that came as far...

1324
02:07:20,432 --> 02:07:23,560 
as from California
and Kansas City...

1325
02:07:23,685 --> 02:07:26,104 
and all the other territories
of the country.

1326
02:07:26,104 --> 02:07:28,607 
Thank you.

1327
02:07:34,238 --> 02:07:36,740 
How did things ever get so far?

1328
02:07:37,783 --> 02:07:40,244 
I don't know.

1329
02:07:41,495 --> 02:07:44,998 
It was so unfortunate
and so unnecessary.

1330
02:07:48,085 --> 02:07:50,295 
Tattaglia lost a son...

1331
02:07:50,295 --> 02:07:52,798 
and I lost a son.

1332
02:07:53,549 --> 02:07:57,136 
We're quits,
and if Tattaglia agrees...

1333
02:07:57,261 --> 02:08:01,306 
then I'm willing to let things
go on the way they were before.

1334
02:08:02,975 --> 02:08:06,478 
We are all grateful to Don Corleone
for calling this meeting.

1335
02:08:06,603 --> 02:08:09,273 
We all know him
as a man of his word.

1336
02:08:09,398 --> 02:08:11,650 
A modest man.
He'll always listen to reason.

1337
02:08:11,650 --> 02:08:14,111 
Yes, Don Barzini.

1338
02:08:14,153 --> 02:08:16,238 
He's too modest.

1339
02:08:16,238 --> 02:08:19,199 
He had all the judges
and politicians in his pocket.

1340
02:08:20,617 --> 02:08:23,454 
He refused to share them.

1341
02:08:23,537 --> 02:08:26,540 
When did I ever refuse
an accommodation?

1342
02:08:27,416 --> 02:08:29,918 
All of you know me here.

1343
02:08:30,794 --> 02:08:34,798 
When did I ever refuse,
except one time?

1344
02:08:34,923 --> 02:08:37,426 
And why?

1345
02:08:37,593 --> 02:08:40,095 
Because I believe
this drug business...

1346
02:08:40,179 --> 02:08:43,307 
is going to destroy us
in the years to come.

1347
02:08:43,432 --> 02:08:47,144 
I mean, it's not like gambling
or liquor or even women...

1348
02:08:47,269 --> 02:08:49,980 
which is something that
most people want nowadays...

1349
02:08:50,105 --> 02:08:53,567 
and is forbidden to them by
the pezzonovante of the church.

1350
02:08:53,692 --> 02:08:56,778 
Even the police departments
that have helped us in the past...

1351
02:08:56,862 --> 02:08:58,697 
with gambling and other things...

1352
02:08:58,697 --> 02:09:02,826 
are gonna refuse to help us
when it comes to narcotics.

1353
02:09:02,951 --> 02:09:05,871 
And I believed that then...

1354
02:09:05,996 --> 02:09:08,123 
and I believe that now.

1355
02:09:08,123 --> 02:09:10,417 
Times have changed.

1356
02:09:10,417 --> 02:09:12,711 
It's not like the old days...

1357
02:09:12,711 --> 02:09:15,172 
when we could do
anything we want.

1358
02:09:15,214 --> 02:09:18,133 
A refusal is not the act of a friend.

1359
02:09:18,217 --> 02:09:22,179 
If Don Corleone had all the judges
and the politicians in New York...

1360
02:09:22,262 --> 02:09:25,265 
then he must share them
or let others use them.

1361
02:09:25,390 --> 02:09:28,519 
He must let us draw
the water from the well.

1362
02:09:29,478 --> 02:09:33,023 
Certainly, he can present a bill
for such services.

1363
02:09:33,148 --> 02:09:35,859 
After all, we are not Communists.

1364
02:09:38,862 --> 02:09:41,907 
I also don't believe in drugs.

1365
02:09:42,032 --> 02:09:44,243 
For years,
I paid my people extra...

1366
02:09:44,243 --> 02:09:46,662 
so they wouldn't do
that kind of business.

1367
02:09:46,662 --> 02:09:50,082 
Somebody comes to them and says,
"I have powders.

1368
02:09:50,207 --> 02:09:52,918 
If you put up a three, four
thousand dollar investment,

1369
02:09:53,919 --> 02:09:56,547 
we can make 50,000 distributing."

1370
02:09:57,673 --> 02:10:01,468 
So they can't resist. I want
to control it as a business...

1371
02:10:01,593 --> 02:10:04,054 
to keep it respectable.

1372
02:10:04,054 --> 02:10:08,559 
I don't want it near schools.
I don't want it sold to children.

1373
02:10:08,684 --> 02:10:11,186 
That's an infamia.

1374
02:10:11,728 --> 02:10:15,649 
In my city, we would keep the traffic
in the dark people, the colored.

1375
02:10:15,774 --> 02:10:18,610 
They're animals anyway,
so let them lose their souls.

1376
02:10:25,617 --> 02:10:28,912 
I hoped that we could come here
and reason together.

1377
02:10:30,622 --> 02:10:33,792 
And as a reasonable man, I'm willing
to do whatever's necessary...

1378
02:10:33,917 --> 02:10:37,379 
to find a peaceful solution
to these problems.

1379
02:10:37,504 --> 02:10:39,673 
Then we are agreed.

1380
02:10:39,673 --> 02:10:42,134 
The traffic in drugs
will be permitted, but controlled.

1381
02:10:42,134 --> 02:10:44,678 
And Don Corleone will give our
protection in the east...

1382
02:10:44,803 --> 02:10:46,722 
and there will be the peace.

1383
02:10:46,722 --> 02:10:50,601 
But I must have strict assurance
from Corleone.

1384
02:10:50,684 --> 02:10:53,854 
As time goes by and
his position becomes stronger...

1385
02:10:53,979 --> 02:10:56,482 
will he attempt
any individual vendetta?

1386
02:10:56,607 --> 02:10:58,650 
Look, we are all
reasonable men here.

1387
02:10:58,650 --> 02:11:02,112 
We don't have to give assurances
as if we were lawyers.

1388
02:11:02,196 --> 02:11:04,448 
You talk about vengeance.

1389
02:11:04,448 --> 02:11:07,701 
Is vengeance gonna bring
your son back to you?

1390
02:11:07,826 --> 02:11:10,287 
Or my boy to me?

1391
02:11:10,996 --> 02:11:13,457 
I forgo the vengeance of my son.

1392
02:11:16,627 --> 02:11:19,129 
But I have selfish reasons.

1393
02:11:21,131 --> 02:11:23,175 
My youngest son...

1394
02:11:23,175 --> 02:11:25,636 
was forced to leave this country...

1395
02:11:26,678 --> 02:11:29,139 
because of this Sollozzo business.

1396
02:11:29,640 --> 02:11:32,476 
All right.
And I have to make arrangements...

1397
02:11:32,559 --> 02:11:37,189 
to bring him back here safely,
cleared of all these false charges.

1398
02:11:38,857 --> 02:11:41,860 
But I'm a superstitious man.

1399
02:11:41,985 --> 02:11:44,530 
And if some unlucky accident
should befall him...

1400
02:11:44,655 --> 02:11:48,367 
if he should get shot
in the head by a police officer...

1401
02:11:48,492 --> 02:11:52,329 
or if he should hang himself
in his jail cell...

1402
02:11:52,412 --> 02:11:54,915 
of if he's struck
by a bolt of lightening...

1403
02:11:56,542 --> 02:11:59,586 
then I'm going to blame
some of the people in this room.

1404
02:12:01,797 --> 02:12:04,299 
And that I do not forgive.

1405
02:12:06,635 --> 02:12:09,138 
But that aside...

1406
02:12:12,057 --> 02:12:14,560 
let me say that I swear...

1407
02:12:16,019 --> 02:12:19,106 
on the souls of my grandchildren...

1408
02:12:19,231 --> 02:12:22,734 
that I will not be the one to break
the peace we've made here today.

1409
02:12:49,136 --> 02:12:51,138 
When I meet with the Tattaglia
people, should I insist...

1410
02:12:51,138 --> 02:12:54,516 
that all these drug middlemen
have clean records?

1411
02:12:54,600 --> 02:12:57,102 
Mention it.
Don't insist.

1412
02:12:58,937 --> 02:13:01,440 
Barzini is a man who'll know that
without being told.

1413
02:13:02,774 --> 02:13:05,402 
You mean Tattaglia.

1414
02:13:05,486 --> 02:13:08,238 
Tattaglia's a pimp.

1415
02:13:08,322 --> 02:13:10,824 
He never could've outfought Santino.

1416
02:13:14,161 --> 02:13:17,831 
But I didn't know until this day
that it was...

1417
02:13:17,956 --> 02:13:20,417 
Barzini all along.

1418
02:13:35,098 --> 02:13:37,601 
Come on, Nancy.

1419
02:13:38,310 --> 02:13:40,771 
Keep together, everyone.
Brian?

1420
02:13:42,147 --> 02:13:44,650 
Okay. All right.

1421
02:13:57,204 --> 02:13:59,748 
How long have you been back?

1422
02:13:59,832 --> 02:14:02,334 
I've been back a year.

1423
02:14:03,293 --> 02:14:05,796 
Longer than that, I think.

1424
02:14:08,048 --> 02:14:10,551 
It's good to see you, Kay.

1425
02:14:16,473 --> 02:14:18,976 
Hi, Miss Adams!

1426
02:14:21,311 --> 02:14:23,814 
I'm working for my father now, Kay.

1427
02:14:26,441 --> 02:14:28,485 
He's been sick.

1428
02:14:28,485 --> 02:14:30,904 
Very sick.

1429
02:14:30,904 --> 02:14:33,031 
But you're not like him, Michael.

1430
02:14:33,031 --> 02:14:35,534 
I thought you weren't going
to become a man like your father.

1431
02:14:35,659 --> 02:14:38,162 
That's what you told me.

1432
02:14:38,704 --> 02:14:41,415 
My father's no different
than any other powerful man.

1433
02:14:43,083 --> 02:14:46,670 
Any man who's responsible
for other people.

1434
02:14:47,754 --> 02:14:50,257 
Like a senator or a president.

1435
02:14:50,257 --> 02:14:52,801 
- Do you know how naive you sound?
- Why?

1436
02:14:52,885 --> 02:14:55,512 
Senators and presidents
don't have men killed.

1437
02:14:56,847 --> 02:14:57,848 
Oh.

1438
02:14:58,849 --> 02:15:01,351 
Who's being naive, Kay?

1439
02:15:01,977 --> 02:15:04,229 
Kay, my father's way
of doing things is over.

1440
02:15:04,229 --> 02:15:07,691 
It's finished.
Even he knows that.

1441
02:15:07,816 --> 02:15:09,860 
I mean, in five years
the Corleone family...

1442
02:15:09,860 --> 02:15:12,362 
is going to be completely legitimate.

1443
02:15:14,114 --> 02:15:16,992 
Trust me. That's all I can tell you
about my business.

1444
02:15:16,992 --> 02:15:17,993 
Kay.

1445
02:15:19,453 --> 02:15:21,830 
Michael, why did you come here?

1446
02:15:21,830 --> 02:15:24,041 
Why?

1447
02:15:24,041 --> 02:15:26,084 
What do you want with me
after all this time...

1448
02:15:26,084 --> 02:15:28,629 
without even calling or writing?

1449
02:15:28,754 --> 02:15:30,756 
I came here because I need you.

1450
02:15:30,756 --> 02:15:33,258 
- Because I care for you.
- Please stop it, Michael.

1451
02:15:33,383 --> 02:15:36,512 
Because I want you to marry me.

1452
02:15:38,013 --> 02:15:40,516 
- It's too late. It's too late.
- Please. Kay.

1453
02:15:42,226 --> 02:15:46,063 
I'll do anything you ask, anything to
make up for what's happened to us.

1454
02:15:47,898 --> 02:15:50,234 
Because that's important, Kay.

1455
02:15:50,234 --> 02:15:53,695 
Because what's important is that...

1456
02:15:53,821 --> 02:15:55,656 
we have each other.

1457
02:15:55,656 --> 02:15:58,575 
That we have a life together.

1458
02:15:58,659 --> 02:16:02,121 
That we have children.
Our children.

1459
02:16:02,621 --> 02:16:03,622 
Kay...

1460
02:16:04,289 --> 02:16:07,000 
I need you...

1461
02:16:07,126 --> 02:16:09,586 
and I love you.

1462
02:16:30,732 --> 02:16:32,734 
Barzini's people
chisel my territory...

1463
02:16:32,734 --> 02:16:34,611 
and we do nothing about it.

1464
02:16:34,611 --> 02:16:37,281 
Pretty soon, there won't be one place
in Brooklyn I can hang my hat.

1465
02:16:37,322 --> 02:16:39,867 
- Just be patient.
- I'm not askin' you for help, Mike.

1466
02:16:39,992 --> 02:16:42,494 
- Just take off the handcuffs.
- Be patient.

1467
02:16:42,619 --> 02:16:44,746 
We gotta protect ourselves.

1468
02:16:44,746 --> 02:16:46,748 
Give me a chance to recruit
some new men.

1469
02:16:46,748 --> 02:16:48,375 
No.

1470
02:16:48,375 --> 02:16:50,878 
I don't wanna give Barzini
an excuse to start fighting.

1471
02:16:50,961 --> 02:16:53,464 
Mike, you're wrong.

1472
02:16:53,589 --> 02:16:57,217 
Don Corleone, you once said
that the day would come...

1473
02:16:57,342 --> 02:17:00,012 
when Tessio and me
could form our own family.

1474
02:17:00,137 --> 02:17:02,139 
Till today,
I would never think of it.

1475
02:17:02,139 --> 02:17:04,516 
I must ask your permission.

1476
02:17:04,516 --> 02:17:07,728 
Well, Michael is now
head of the family...

1477
02:17:07,853 --> 02:17:10,522 
and if he gives his permission,
then you have my blessing.

1478
02:17:12,107 --> 02:17:14,610 
After we make the move to Nevada...

1479
02:17:14,693 --> 02:17:17,696 
you can break off from the Corleone
family and go on your own.

1480
02:17:17,821 --> 02:17:20,616 
- After we make the move to Nevada.
- How long will that be?

1481
02:17:21,867 --> 02:17:23,494 
Six months.

1482
02:17:23,494 --> 02:17:26,955 
Forgive me, Godfather,
but with you gone...

1483
02:17:27,039 --> 02:17:30,042 
me and Pete'll come under
Barzini's thumb sooner or later.

1484
02:17:30,125 --> 02:17:32,628 
And I hate that goddamn Barzini.

1485
02:17:32,669 --> 02:17:35,589 
In six months' time, there won't be
nothing left to build on.

1486
02:17:35,714 --> 02:17:38,675 
- You have faith in my judgment?
- Yes.

1487
02:17:38,801 --> 02:17:41,595 
- Do I have your loyalty?
- Yes, always, Godfather.

1488
02:17:41,720 --> 02:17:43,972 
Then be a friend to Michael...

1489
02:17:43,972 --> 02:17:46,475 
and do as he says.

1490
02:17:49,895 --> 02:17:52,105 
There are things being negotiated
now that are going to solve...

1491
02:17:52,105 --> 02:17:55,192 
all your problems
and answer all your questions.

1492
02:17:55,317 --> 02:17:57,820 
That's all I can tell you now.

1493
02:17:58,320 --> 02:18:00,948 
Carlo, you grew up in Nevada.

1494
02:18:01,073 --> 02:18:04,201 
When we make our move there,
you're gonna be my right-hand man.

1495
02:18:04,326 --> 02:18:07,037 
Tom Hagen's no longer consigliere.

1496
02:18:07,121 --> 02:18:09,623 
He's gonna be our lawyer in Vegas.

1497
02:18:09,623 --> 02:18:12,084 
That's no reflection on Tom,
but that's the way I want it.

1498
02:18:12,084 --> 02:18:14,044 
Besides, if I ever need help...

1499
02:18:14,044 --> 02:18:16,338 
who's a better consigliere
than my father?

1500
02:18:16,338 --> 02:18:18,841 
Now that's it.

1501
02:18:36,942 --> 02:18:39,403 
- Thank you, Papa.
- I'm happy for you, Carlo.

1502
02:18:40,821 --> 02:18:45,075 
Mike, ehh...
Why am I out?

1503
02:18:45,159 --> 02:18:47,661 
You're not a wartime consigliere, Tom.

1504
02:18:49,246 --> 02:18:51,748 
Things may get rough
with the move we're trying.

1505
02:18:52,416 --> 02:18:53,417 
Tom...

1506
02:18:59,006 --> 02:19:01,300 
I advised Michael.

1507
02:19:01,300 --> 02:19:04,178 
I never thought
you were a bad consigliere.

1508
02:19:04,303 --> 02:19:07,556 
I thought Santino was a bad Don...

1509
02:19:07,639 --> 02:19:09,933 
rest in peace.

1510
02:19:09,933 --> 02:19:12,936 
Michael has all my confidence,
as, as you do.

1511
02:19:14,146 --> 02:19:17,691 
But there are reasons why
you must have no part...

1512
02:19:17,816 --> 02:19:20,027 
in what is going to happen.

1513
02:19:20,027 --> 02:19:21,528 
Maybe I could help.

1514
02:19:21,528 --> 02:19:24,031 
You're out, Tom.

1515
02:20:12,454 --> 02:20:14,957 
I can't get over the way
your face looks.

1516
02:20:15,082 --> 02:20:18,252 
It really looks good.
This doctor did some job.

1517
02:20:18,377 --> 02:20:21,004 
Who talked you into it, Kay?
Hey, hey, wait.

1518
02:20:21,088 --> 02:20:23,507 
Leave them out here.
We'll deal with them later.

1519
02:20:23,507 --> 02:20:25,509 
He's tired.
He wants to clean up.

1520
02:20:25,509 --> 02:20:28,554 
All right now, let me open the door.
All right?

1521
02:20:34,101 --> 02:20:36,436 
Hello, Mike.
Welcome to Las Vegas.

1522
02:20:36,436 --> 02:20:39,690 
All for you, kid.
It was all his idea, right?

1523
02:20:39,815 --> 02:20:42,609 
- Well, your brother, Freddy...
- It was... Girls?

1524
02:20:46,363 --> 02:20:49,158 
I'll be right back.
You keep them occupied.

1525
02:20:49,241 --> 02:20:52,202 
That a boy.
Anything you want, kid, anything. Huh?

1526
02:20:52,286 --> 02:20:54,788 
Who are the girls?

1527
02:20:55,372 --> 02:20:57,374 
That's for you to find out.

1528
02:20:57,374 --> 02:21:00,210 
Get rid of them, Fredo.

1529
02:21:00,335 --> 02:21:02,463 
- Hey, Mike...
- Fredo, I'm here on business.

1530
02:21:02,463 --> 02:21:06,216 
I leave tomorrow.
Now, get rid of them. I'm tired.

1531
02:21:06,300 --> 02:21:08,802 
Get rid of the band too.

1532
02:21:13,765 --> 02:21:16,560 
Hey, just take off.
Come on. Let's go.

1533
02:21:16,685 --> 02:21:19,938 
Hey, that's it.
Hey, Angelo, that's it.

1534
02:21:20,063 --> 02:21:22,065 
Let's go.
Hey, come on!

1535
02:21:22,107 --> 02:21:24,568 
Scram!

1536
02:21:24,860 --> 02:21:27,237 
Come on, honey. Let's go.
I don't know, Johnny.

1537
02:21:27,237 --> 02:21:29,406 
I don't know what the hell's
the matter with him. I'm sorry.

1538
02:21:29,406 --> 02:21:31,700 
It's all right, Freddy.

1539
02:21:31,700 --> 02:21:34,203 
I don't know.
He's tired, he's hot.

1540
02:21:41,210 --> 02:21:43,712 
What happened to Moe Greene?

1541
02:21:44,296 --> 02:21:46,799 
He said he had some business.
He said give him a call...

1542
02:21:46,799 --> 02:21:48,801 
when the party started.

1543
02:21:48,801 --> 02:21:51,261 
Well, give him a call.

1544
02:21:52,095 --> 02:21:55,182 
- Johnny, how are you?
- Hello, Mike. Nice to see you again.

1545
02:21:55,307 --> 02:21:57,434 
- We're all proud of you.
- Thanks, Mike.

1546
02:21:57,476 --> 02:21:59,853 
Sit down, Johnny.
I want to talk to you.

1547
02:21:59,853 --> 02:22:04,274 
- The Don's proud of you, too, Johnny.
- Well, I, owe it all to him.

1548
02:22:04,399 --> 02:22:06,443 
Well, he knows
how grateful you are.

1549
02:22:06,443 --> 02:22:09,488 
That's why he'd like to ask
a favor of you.

1550
02:22:09,613 --> 02:22:12,116 
Mike, what can I do?

1551
02:22:12,908 --> 02:22:15,452 
The Corleone family is thinking
of giving up all its interests...

1552
02:22:15,494 --> 02:22:18,872 
in the olive oil business,
settling out here.

1553
02:22:18,997 --> 02:22:22,251 
Now, Moe Greene will sell us his
share of the casino and the hotel...

1554
02:22:22,334 --> 02:22:24,962 
so it can be completely owned
by the family. Tom?

1555
02:22:25,045 --> 02:22:27,339 
Hey, Mike, are you sure about that?

1556
02:22:27,339 --> 02:22:30,217 
Moe loves the business. He never
said nothin' to me about sellin'.

1557
02:22:30,342 --> 02:22:32,803 
Well, I'll make him an offer
he can't refuse.

1558
02:22:34,555 --> 02:22:36,974 
See, Johnny...

1559
02:22:37,015 --> 02:22:39,309 
see, we figure that entertainment
will be a big factor...

1560
02:22:39,309 --> 02:22:41,103 
in drawing gamblers to the casino.

1561
02:22:41,103 --> 02:22:44,398 
Now we hope you'll sign a contract
to appear five times a year.

1562
02:22:47,901 --> 02:22:51,155 
Perhaps convince some of
your friends in the movies...

1563
02:22:51,280 --> 02:22:53,782 
to do the same.

1564
02:22:53,866 --> 02:22:56,326 
We're counting on you.

1565
02:22:57,953 --> 02:23:00,456 
Sure, Mike.
I'll do anything for my godfather.

1566
02:23:00,581 --> 02:23:01,915 
You know that.

1567
02:23:01,915 --> 02:23:04,418 
Good.

1568
02:23:04,543 --> 02:23:06,795 
Hey, Mike.
Hello, fellas.

1569
02:23:06,795 --> 02:23:10,507 
Everybody's here. Freddy, Tom.
Good to see you, Mike.

1570
02:23:10,591 --> 02:23:12,634 
- How are you, Moe?
- You got everything you want?

1571
02:23:12,634 --> 02:23:15,345 
The chef cooked for you special, the
dancers will kick your tongue out...

1572
02:23:15,429 --> 02:23:17,181 
and your credit is good.

1573
02:23:17,222 --> 02:23:19,850 
Draw chips for everybody in the room
so they can play on the house.

1574
02:23:23,395 --> 02:23:25,898 
My credit good enough
to buy you out?

1575
02:23:27,900 --> 02:23:29,818 
Buy me out?

1576
02:23:29,818 --> 02:23:32,488 
The casino. The hotel.

1577
02:23:32,571 --> 02:23:35,365 
The Corleone family
wants to buy you out.

1578
02:23:35,449 --> 02:23:38,327 
The Corleone family
wants to buy me out?

1579
02:23:38,410 --> 02:23:40,913 
No, I buy you out.
You don't buy me out.

1580
02:23:40,954 --> 02:23:44,208 
Your casino loses money.
Maybe we can do better.

1581
02:23:44,333 --> 02:23:46,835 
You think I'm skimming
off the top, Mike?

1582
02:23:47,628 --> 02:23:50,130 
You're unlucky.

1583
02:23:53,300 --> 02:23:55,761 
You goddamn guineas
really make me laugh.

1584
02:23:55,761 --> 02:23:58,597 
I do you a favor and take Freddy in
when you're having a bad time.

1585
02:23:58,722 --> 02:24:01,183 
- And then you try to push me out!
- Wait a minute.

1586
02:24:01,183 --> 02:24:03,769 
You took Freddy in because
the Corleone family...

1587
02:24:03,894 --> 02:24:06,396 
bankrolled your casino,
because the Molinari family...

1588
02:24:06,480 --> 02:24:08,607 
on the coast guaranteed his safety.

1589
02:24:08,607 --> 02:24:10,692 
Now, we're talkin' business.
Let's talk business.

1590
02:24:10,692 --> 02:24:13,403 
Yeah, let's talk business, Mike.
First of all, you're all done.

1591
02:24:13,529 --> 02:24:15,989 
The Corleone family don't even have
that kind of muscle anymore.

1592
02:24:15,989 --> 02:24:18,492 
The Godfather's sick, right? You're
getting chased out of New York...

1593
02:24:18,534 --> 02:24:20,327 
by Barzini and the other families.

1594
02:24:20,327 --> 02:24:24,248 
What do you think is going on here? You think
you can come to my hotel and take over?

1595
02:24:24,331 --> 02:24:26,166 
I talked to Barzini.

1596
02:24:26,166 --> 02:24:29,419 
I can make a deal with him
and still keep my hotel.

1597
02:24:29,545 --> 02:24:32,131 
Is that why you slapped
my brother around in public?

1598
02:24:33,215 --> 02:24:34,925 
Oh, no, that was nothin', Mike.

1599
02:24:35,217 --> 02:24:37,761 
Now, now, Moe didn't mean nothin' by that.

1600
02:24:37,886 --> 02:24:40,389 
Sure he flies off the handle
once in a while...

1601
02:24:40,389 --> 02:24:42,516 
but Moe and me,
we're good friends, right, Moe, huh?

1602
02:24:42,516 --> 02:24:44,393 
I got a business to run.

1603
02:24:44,393 --> 02:24:47,104 
I gotta kick asses sometimes
to make it run right.

1604
02:24:47,229 --> 02:24:51,233 
We had a little argument, Freddy and I,
so I had to straighten him out.

1605
02:24:51,316 --> 02:24:53,944 
You straightened my brother out?

1606
02:24:54,027 --> 02:24:56,530 
He was banging cocktail waitresses
two at a time!

1607
02:24:56,530 --> 02:24:59,450 
Players couldn't get a drink at the table.
What's wrong with you?

1608
02:25:05,497 --> 02:25:08,959 
I leave for New York tomorrow.
Think about a price.

1609
02:25:09,084 --> 02:25:10,794 
Son of a bitch.

1610
02:25:10,794 --> 02:25:13,797 
Do you know who I am?
I'm Moe Greene.

1611
02:25:13,922 --> 02:25:16,508 
I made my bones when you were
going out with cheerleaders.

1612
02:25:16,633 --> 02:25:19,136 
Wait a minute, Moe.
Moe, I got an idea.

1613
02:25:20,137 --> 02:25:23,307 
Tom, you're the consigliere.
Now, you can talk to the Don.

1614
02:25:23,432 --> 02:25:25,434 
- You can explain...
- Just a minute.

1615
02:25:25,434 --> 02:25:29,021 
The Don is semiretired and Mike is
in charge of the family business now.

1616
02:25:29,146 --> 02:25:31,690 
If you have anything to say,
say it to Michael.

1617
02:25:36,570 --> 02:25:41,158 
Mike! You don't come to Las Vegas and
talk to a man like Moe Greene like that!

1618
02:25:43,535 --> 02:25:48,248 
Fredo. You're my older brother,
and I love you.

1619
02:25:49,750 --> 02:25:51,835 
But don't ever take sides
with anyone...

1620
02:25:51,835 --> 02:25:54,713 
against the family again...

1621
02:25:54,838 --> 02:25:57,341 
ever.

1622
02:26:04,139 --> 02:26:06,308 
I have to see my father
and his people.

1623
02:26:06,308 --> 02:26:08,811 
- So have dinner without me.
- Oh, Michael.

1624
02:26:10,312 --> 02:26:12,564 
This weekend we'll go out.
We'll go to the city.

1625
02:26:12,564 --> 02:26:15,067 
We'll see a show and we'll have dinner.
I promise.

1626
02:26:22,533 --> 02:26:25,410 
Oh, Michael. Michael, your sister wants
to ask you something.

1627
02:26:25,536 --> 02:26:27,663 
- Well, let her ask.
- No, she's afraid to.

1628
02:26:27,663 --> 02:26:30,874 
Connie and Carlo want you to be
godfather to their little boy.

1629
02:26:30,999 --> 02:26:32,876 
- Oh, we'll see.
- Will you?

1630
02:26:32,876 --> 02:26:35,379 
Let me think about it. We'll see.
Come on.

1631
02:26:41,969 --> 02:26:43,887 
So...

1632
02:26:43,929 --> 02:26:46,890 
Barzini will move against you first.

1633
02:26:46,974 --> 02:26:51,311 
He'll set up a meeting with
someone that you absolutely trust...

1634
02:26:51,436 --> 02:26:53,897 
guaranteeing your safety.

1635
02:26:54,773 --> 02:26:58,026 
And at that meeting,
you'll be assassinated.

1636
02:27:02,656 --> 02:27:05,868 
I like to drink wine
more than I used to.

1637
02:27:07,035 --> 02:27:09,204 
Anyway, I'm drinking more.

1638
02:27:09,204 --> 02:27:11,707 
It's good for you, Pop.

1639
02:27:15,627 --> 02:27:18,130 
I don't know.

1640
02:27:19,047 --> 02:27:21,550 
Your wife and children,
are you happy with them?

1641
02:27:22,968 --> 02:27:25,012 
Very happy.

1642
02:27:25,012 --> 02:27:27,556 
That's good.

1643
02:27:27,639 --> 02:27:29,933 
I hope you don't mind
the way I...

1644
02:27:29,933 --> 02:27:32,519 
I keep going over
this Barzini business.

1645
02:27:32,644 --> 02:27:34,688 
No, not at all.

1646
02:27:34,688 --> 02:27:37,065 
It's an old habit.

1647
02:27:37,065 --> 02:27:39,818 
I spent my life
tryin' not to be careless.

1648
02:27:41,695 --> 02:27:44,531 
Women and children can be careless,
but not men.

1649
02:27:48,410 --> 02:27:50,954 
- How's your boy?
- He's good.

1650
02:27:51,079 --> 02:27:53,582 
You know, he looks
more like you every day.

1651
02:27:56,376 --> 02:27:58,629 
He's smarter than I am.

1652
02:27:58,670 --> 02:28:01,131 
Three years old,
he can read the funny papers.

1653
02:28:02,966 --> 02:28:05,469 
Reads the funny papers.

1654
02:28:12,184 --> 02:28:14,686 
I want you to arrange
to have a telephone man...

1655
02:28:14,686 --> 02:28:17,815 
check all the calls that go
in and out of here.

1656
02:28:17,940 --> 02:28:20,067 
- I did it already, Pop.
- Could be anyone.

1657
02:28:20,067 --> 02:28:23,612 
- Pop, I took care of that.
- Oh, that's right. I forgot.

1658
02:28:27,324 --> 02:28:29,701 
What's the matter?

1659
02:28:29,701 --> 02:28:32,204 
What's bothering you?

1660
02:28:34,998 --> 02:28:37,501 
I'll handle it.

1661
02:28:37,876 --> 02:28:40,379 
I told you I can handle it,
I'll handle it.

1662
02:28:53,433 --> 02:28:57,771 
I knew that Santino was gonna
have to go through all this...

1663
02:28:57,896 --> 02:28:59,773 
and Fredo...

1664
02:28:59,773 --> 02:29:02,234 
Well...

1665
02:29:02,234 --> 02:29:04,736 
Fredo was...

1666
02:29:06,280 --> 02:29:09,032 
But I never, I never wanted this for you.

1667
02:29:11,326 --> 02:29:14,163 
I worked my whole life...
I don't apologize...

1668
02:29:14,246 --> 02:29:16,415 
to take care of my family...

1669
02:29:16,415 --> 02:29:20,294 
and I refused to be a fool...

1670
02:29:20,419 --> 02:29:24,465 
dancing on a string
held by all those big shots.

1671
02:29:26,592 --> 02:29:29,720 
I don't apologize. That's my life.
But I thought that...

1672
02:29:31,722 --> 02:29:34,308 
that when it was your time...

1673
02:29:34,433 --> 02:29:36,894 
that you would be the one
to hold the strings.

1674
02:29:38,770 --> 02:29:41,231 
Senator Corleone.

1675
02:29:42,232 --> 02:29:44,401 
Governor Corleone.
Something.

1676
02:29:44,401 --> 02:29:46,904 
Another pezzonovante.

1677
02:29:52,409 --> 02:29:56,246 
Just wasn't enough time, Michael.
Wasn't enough time.

1678
02:29:56,330 --> 02:29:58,916 
We'll get there, Pop.

1679
02:29:59,041 --> 02:30:01,543 
We'll get there.

1680
02:30:04,797 --> 02:30:09,134 
Now listen. Whoever comes to you
with this Barzini meeting...

1681
02:30:09,259 --> 02:30:11,011 
he's the traitor.

1682
02:30:11,011 --> 02:30:13,514 
Don't forget that.

1683
02:30:29,279 --> 02:30:31,782 
Put it over the tree.

1684
02:30:46,547 --> 02:30:49,007 
- Can I water these?
- Yeah.

1685
02:30:49,007 --> 02:30:50,592 
That's fine.

1686
02:30:50,592 --> 02:30:53,095 
Over here.
Over here.

1687
02:30:55,180 --> 02:30:57,683 
Be careful.
You're spilling it.

1688
02:31:04,022 --> 02:31:06,483 
Anthony, come here.

1689
02:31:11,905 --> 02:31:14,408 
Go ahead. That's right.
We'll put it right there.

1690
02:31:20,205 --> 02:31:22,708 
I'll show you something.
Come here.

1691
02:31:25,210 --> 02:31:27,713 
Now, you stand there.

1692
02:31:30,841 --> 02:31:33,343 
Give me an orange!

1693
02:31:50,903 --> 02:31:53,405 
That's a new trick.

1694
02:31:53,989 --> 02:31:56,533 
You run in there.
Run in there.

1695
02:32:09,171 --> 02:32:11,673 
- Where are you?
- Who?

1696
02:32:44,790 --> 02:32:47,292 
Ouch!

1697
02:35:08,851 --> 02:35:11,353 
Mike, can I have a minute?

1698
02:35:21,697 --> 02:35:24,158 
Barzini wants to arrange a meeting.

1699
02:35:24,158 --> 02:35:26,660 
He says we can straighten
any of our problems out.

1700
02:35:28,328 --> 02:35:30,831 
- You talked to him?
- Yeah.

1701
02:35:31,748 --> 02:35:34,209 
I can arrange security...

1702
02:35:34,209 --> 02:35:36,712 
on my territory.

1703
02:35:38,630 --> 02:35:40,632 
All right?

1704
02:35:40,632 --> 02:35:43,469 
- All right.
- All right.

1705
02:35:58,776 --> 02:36:01,278 
Do you know how
they're gonna come at you?

1706
02:36:04,198 --> 02:36:06,617 
They're arranging a meeting
in Brooklyn.

1707
02:36:06,658 --> 02:36:09,119 
Tessio's ground...

1708
02:36:09,995 --> 02:36:12,498 
where I'll be safe.

1709
02:36:24,051 --> 02:36:27,638 
I always thought it would've been
Clemenza, not Tessio.

1710
02:36:27,763 --> 02:36:30,140 
It's the smart move.

1711
02:36:30,140 --> 02:36:32,643 
Tessio was always smarter.

1712
02:36:33,811 --> 02:36:36,146 
But I'm gonna wait.

1713
02:36:36,146 --> 02:36:38,649 
After the baptism.

1714
02:36:40,609 --> 02:36:43,153 
I've decided to be godfather
to Connie's baby.

1715
02:36:44,530 --> 02:36:47,449 
And then I'll meet
with Don Barzini...

1716
02:36:47,533 --> 02:36:49,993 
and Tattaglia...

1717
02:36:49,993 --> 02:36:52,496 
all the heads
of the five families.

1718
02:37:19,022 --> 02:37:21,024 
Go forth from him, unclean spirit,

1719
02:37:21,233 --> 02:37:24,403 
and give place to the Holy Spirit,
the Spirit of God.

1720
02:37:26,405 --> 02:37:27,406 
Let us pray.

1721
02:37:27,406 --> 02:37:30,409 
Our prayers through through
Christ our Lord. So be it.

1722
02:37:31,034 --> 02:37:32,035 
Michael.

1723
02:37:32,035 --> 02:37:35,038 
Signed with the sign of the Lord's cross,

1724
02:37:36,039 --> 02:37:39,001 
so that, preserving this first experience
of the greatness of thy glory,

1725
02:37:39,042 --> 02:37:42,004 
he may deserve, by keeping
thy commandments,

1726
02:37:42,004 --> 02:37:45,007 
<i>to attain to the glory of regeneration.</i>

1727
02:37:45,007 --> 02:37:48,010 
<i>Through Christ our Lord. So be it.</i>

1728
02:37:48,010 --> 02:37:51,013 
<i>Let us pray.</i>
Almighty, everlasting God,

1729
02:37:51,013 --> 02:37:53,515 
<i>Father of our Lord Jesus Christ,</i>

1730
02:37:53,515 --> 02:37:56,518 
<i>look graciously down upon this,</i>
thy servant, Michael.

1731
02:37:56,518 --> 02:37:59,521 
Who shall come to judge the living
and the dead,

1732
02:37:59,521 --> 02:38:02,524 
and the world by fire. So be it.

1733
02:38:02,524 --> 02:38:04,818 
Michael. Receive the salt of wisdom.

1734
02:38:04,818 --> 02:38:07,112 
Let it be to thee a token of mercy
unto everlasting life.

1735
02:38:07,112 --> 02:38:09,114 
May it make your way easy to eternal life.
So be it.

1736
02:38:09,114 --> 02:38:11,617 
May the almighty God, the Father
of our Lord Jesus Christ,

1737
02:38:11,617 --> 02:38:14,119 
<i>Who hath regenerated thee by water</i>
and the Holy Spirit,

1738
02:38:15,120 --> 02:38:17,623 
<i>and who hath given thee the</i>
remission of all thy sins,

1739
02:38:18,123 --> 02:38:21,627 
<i>may he, himself anoint thee with</i>
the Chrism of Salvation,

1740
02:38:21,627 --> 02:38:24,630 
<i>in the same Christ Jesus our Lord,</i>
unto life eternal. So be it.

1741
02:38:25,631 --> 02:38:28,926 
I annoint you with the oil of salvation
in Christ Jesus our Lord,

1742
02:38:29,259 --> 02:38:32,221 
that you may have everlasting life.
So be it.

1743
02:38:39,645 --> 02:38:42,648 
<i>Do you believe in the Holy Ghost,</i>
the Holy Catholic Church,

1744
02:38:42,648 --> 02:38:45,651 
<i>the communion of Saints,</i>
the forgiveness of sins,

1745
02:38:45,651 --> 02:38:49,154 
<i>the resurrection of the body</i>
and life everlasting? I do believe.

1746
02:38:50,155 --> 02:38:53,158 
I exorcise thee, unclean spirit,
in the name of the Father,

1747
02:38:53,158 --> 02:38:56,161 
and of the Son, and of the Holy Spirit,

1748
02:38:56,161 --> 02:39:00,165 
that thou goest out and depart from
this servant of God, Michael.

1749
02:39:00,165 --> 02:39:03,627 
For he commands thee, accursed one,

1750
02:39:05,462 --> 02:39:08,465 
Be opened, for an odor of sweetness.

1751
02:39:08,465 --> 02:39:11,468 
Be thou, devil, begone,

1752
02:39:11,468 --> 02:39:13,762 
for the judgment of God shall draw near.

1753
02:39:13,804 --> 02:39:16,682 
Michael, do you believe in God,
the Father almighty...

1754
02:39:16,807 --> 02:39:19,768 
- creator of Heaven and Earth?
- I do.

1755
02:39:19,852 --> 02:39:23,147 
<i>Do you believe in Jesus Christ,</i>
his only Son, our Lord?

1756
02:39:23,272 --> 02:39:24,773 
<i>I do.</i>

1757
02:39:24,773 --> 02:39:28,944 
<i>Do you believe in the Holy Ghost,</i>
the Holy Catholic Church?

1758
02:39:28,944 --> 02:39:29,945 
<i>I do.</i>

1759
02:39:30,237 --> 02:39:34,158 
<i>Our Father, who art in heaven,</i>
hallowed be thy name.

1760
02:39:34,158 --> 02:39:38,162 
<i>Thy kingdom come. Thy will be done,</i>
on earth as it is in heaven.

1761
02:39:38,162 --> 02:39:40,956 
<i>Give us this day our daily bread.</i>

1762
02:39:40,956 --> 02:39:42,958 
<i>And forgive us our trespasses,</i>

1763
02:39:43,125 --> 02:39:46,253 
<i>as we forgive them that</i>
trespass against us.

1764
02:39:46,253 --> 02:39:49,256 
<i>And lead us not into temptation,</i>

1765
02:39:49,256 --> 02:39:51,258 
<i>but deliver us from evil.</i>
So be it.

1766
02:39:51,258 --> 02:39:52,759 
Michael.

1767
02:39:52,759 --> 02:39:55,762 
Enter thou into the temple of God,

1768
02:39:55,762 --> 02:39:58,724 
that thou mayest have part with Christ
unto life everlasting. So be it.

1769
02:39:58,724 --> 02:40:01,226 
I believe in God the Father almighty,

1770
02:40:01,226 --> 02:40:03,228 
Creator of heaven and earth,

1771
02:40:03,228 --> 02:40:06,732 
<i>and in Jesus Christ his only</i>
son our Lord,

1772
02:40:06,732 --> 02:40:09,067 
<i>who was conceived by the Holy Ghost,</i>

1773
02:40:09,067 --> 02:40:11,028 
<i>born of the Virgin Mary,</i>

1774
02:40:11,069 --> 02:40:14,364 
<i>suffered under Pontius Pilate,</i>
was crucified, dead, and buried.

1775
02:40:14,364 --> 02:40:17,034 
<i>He descended into Hell.</i>
On the third day,

1776
02:40:17,034 --> 02:40:21,038 
<i>He rose again from the dead.</i>
He ascended into heaven,

1777
02:40:21,038 --> 02:40:23,832 
<i>and sitteth at the right hand of</i>
God the Father almighty,

1778
02:40:23,874 --> 02:40:26,335 
<i>from thence shall he come to judge</i>
the living and the dead.

1779
02:40:26,335 --> 02:40:29,338 
<i>I believe in the Holy Ghost,</i>
the Holy Catholic Church,

1780
02:40:29,338 --> 02:40:32,341 
<i>the communion of saints,</i>
the forgiveness of sins,

1781
02:40:32,341 --> 02:40:35,177 
<i>the resurrection of the body,</i>
and life everlasting. So be it.

1782
02:40:35,219 --> 02:40:40,182 
Michael Francis Rizzi,
do you renounce Satan?

1783
02:40:46,563 --> 02:40:49,066 
I do renounce him.

1784
02:40:57,407 --> 02:40:59,910 
And all his works?

1785
02:41:12,089 --> 02:41:14,591 
I do renounce them.

1786
02:41:19,471 --> 02:41:23,434 
- And all his pomps?
- I do renounce them.

1787
02:41:38,824 --> 02:41:42,911 
Michael Rizzi,
will you be baptized?

1788
02:41:42,995 --> 02:41:44,997 
I will.

1789
02:41:44,997 --> 02:41:47,291 
In the name of the Father,

1790
02:41:47,291 --> 02:41:49,293 
<i>and of the Son,</i>

1791
02:41:49,293 --> 02:41:51,712 
<i>and of the Holy Spirit.</i>

1792
02:41:52,045 --> 02:41:54,590 
<i>Michael Rizzi, go in peace.</i>

1793
02:41:54,715 --> 02:41:57,759 
And may the Lord be with you.
So be it.

1794
02:42:39,843 --> 02:42:41,845 
- Carlo.
- What?

1795
02:42:41,845 --> 02:42:44,097 
Can't go to Vegas.
Something's come up.

1796
02:42:44,097 --> 02:42:46,141 
Everybody's gonna have to leave
without us.

1797
02:42:46,141 --> 02:42:48,685 
- It's our first vacation together.
- Connie, please.

1798
02:42:48,811 --> 02:42:50,813 
- What do you wanna do?
- Go back to the house.

1799
02:42:50,813 --> 02:42:53,690 
Wait for my call.
It's important.

1800
02:42:53,774 --> 02:42:56,276 
I'll only be a couple of days.

1801
02:42:58,695 --> 02:43:01,198 
Have a nice trip, Mama.

1802
02:43:12,209 --> 02:43:14,711 
We're on our way to Brooklyn.

1803
02:43:16,547 --> 02:43:18,966 
I hope Mike can get us
a good deal tonight.

1804
02:43:18,966 --> 02:43:21,468 
I'm sure he will.

1805
02:43:28,225 --> 02:43:31,228 
Sal, Tom, the boss says
he'll come in a separate car.

1806
02:43:31,353 --> 02:43:33,564 
He says for you two
to go on ahead.

1807
02:43:33,564 --> 02:43:36,191 
Hell, he can't do that.
It screws up all my arrangements.

1808
02:43:36,275 --> 02:43:38,777 
- Well that's what he said.
- I can't go either, Sal.

1809
02:43:51,415 --> 02:43:54,168 
Tell Mike it was only business.

1810
02:43:54,251 --> 02:43:56,753 
I always liked him.

1811
02:43:56,920 --> 02:43:59,423 
- He understands that.
- Excuse me, Sal.

1812
02:44:05,846 --> 02:44:08,348 
Tom, can you get me off the hook?

1813
02:44:09,433 --> 02:44:12,144 
- For old times' sake.
- Can't do it, Sally.

1814
02:44:58,107 --> 02:45:00,609 
You have to answer
for Santino, Carlo.

1815
02:45:05,489 --> 02:45:07,324 
Mike, you got it all wrong.

1816
02:45:07,324 --> 02:45:09,827 
You fingered Sonny
for the Barzini people.

1817
02:45:11,453 --> 02:45:14,498 
That little farce you played
with my sister.

1818
02:45:14,623 --> 02:45:16,625 
Did you think that could fool
a Corleone?

1819
02:45:16,625 --> 02:45:19,795 
Mike, I'm innocent.
I swear on the kids.

1820
02:45:19,878 --> 02:45:22,381 
- Please, don't do this to me.
- Sit down.

1821
02:45:25,509 --> 02:45:28,011 
Don't do this to me, please.

1822
02:45:36,895 --> 02:45:39,398 
Barzini's dead.

1823
02:45:40,566 --> 02:45:43,068 
So is Phillip Tattaglia...

1824
02:45:44,278 --> 02:45:46,780 
Moe Greene...

1825
02:45:46,780 --> 02:45:49,283 
Stracci...

1826
02:45:49,867 --> 02:45:52,369 
Cuneo.

1827
02:45:52,411 --> 02:45:55,914 
Today I settle all family business,
so don't tell me you're innocent, Carlo.

1828
02:45:57,791 --> 02:46:00,294 
Admit what you did.

1829
02:46:03,422 --> 02:46:05,924 
Get him a drink.

1830
02:46:11,555 --> 02:46:14,016 
Come on.

1831
02:46:14,016 --> 02:46:16,393 
Don't be afraid, Carlo.

1832
02:46:16,393 --> 02:46:18,896 
Come on. You think I'd make my sister
a widow?

1833
02:46:20,564 --> 02:46:23,066 
I'm godfather to your son, Carlo.

1834
02:46:30,199 --> 02:46:31,533 
Go ahead, drink.

1835
02:46:31,533 --> 02:46:34,036 
Drink.

1836
02:46:37,080 --> 02:46:39,249 
Now, Carlo, you're out
of the family business.

1837
02:46:39,249 --> 02:46:42,920 
That's your punishment.
You're finished.

1838
02:46:43,045 --> 02:46:45,547 
I'm putting you on a plane to Vegas.

1839
02:46:51,762 --> 02:46:55,182 
I want you to stay there.
Understand?

1840
02:46:55,265 --> 02:46:57,768 
Only don't tell me
you're innocent...

1841
02:46:59,353 --> 02:47:02,314 
because it insults my intelligence.

1842
02:47:02,439 --> 02:47:04,942 
It makes me very angry.

1843
02:47:07,820 --> 02:47:11,073 
Now, who approached you?

1844
02:47:11,156 --> 02:47:13,659 
Tattaglia or Barzini?

1845
02:47:20,791 --> 02:47:23,293 
It was Barzini.

1846
02:47:25,754 --> 02:47:28,257 
Good.

1847
02:47:34,888 --> 02:47:37,558 
There's a car waiting for you
outside to take you to the airport.

1848
02:47:38,976 --> 02:47:41,478 
I'll call your wife,
tell her what flight you're on.

1849
02:47:47,109 --> 02:47:49,611 
- Please, can I...
- Get out of my sight.

1850
02:48:15,053 --> 02:48:17,556 
Hello, Carlo.

1851
02:49:14,071 --> 02:49:16,907 
Will you stop crying?
What are you trying to tell me?

1852
02:49:16,990 --> 02:49:19,785 
- I'm trying to tell you you're wrong.
- Mama, please!

1853
02:49:28,210 --> 02:49:30,212 
Michael! Michael!

1854
02:49:30,712 --> 02:49:33,215 
Where is he?

1855
02:49:35,092 --> 02:49:40,139 
Michael, you lousy bastard!
You killed my husband!

1856
02:49:40,264 --> 02:49:42,850 
You waited until Papa died
so nobody could stop you...

1857
02:49:42,933 --> 02:49:44,476 
and then you killed him!

1858
02:49:44,476 --> 02:49:47,604 
You blamed him for Sonny.
You always did. Everybody did.

1859
02:49:47,729 --> 02:49:51,358 
But you never thought about me!
You never gave a damn about me!

1860
02:49:51,442 --> 02:49:53,944 
Now what am I gonna do?

1861
02:49:57,656 --> 02:50:00,159 
Why do you think
he kept Carlo at the mall?

1862
02:50:00,242 --> 02:50:02,786 
All the time he knew
he was gonna kill him.

1863
02:50:02,911 --> 02:50:05,998 
And you stood godfather
to our baby.

1864
02:50:06,123 --> 02:50:08,459 
You lousy, coldhearted bastard.

1865
02:50:08,459 --> 02:50:10,961 
Want to know how many men
he had killed with Carlo?

1866
02:50:10,961 --> 02:50:12,754 
Read the papers!
Read the papers!

1867
02:50:12,754 --> 02:50:15,257 
That's your husband!
That's your husband!

1868
02:50:28,812 --> 02:50:31,315 
Take her upstairs.

1869
02:50:31,356 --> 02:50:33,859 
- Get her a doctor.
